1
00:00:33,987 --> 00:00:38,791
He is water, fire, and wind.

2
00:00:38,791 --> 00:00:40,826
He is light and darkness.

3
00:00:42,095 --> 00:00:44,029
And once...

4
00:00:50,537 --> 00:00:52,237
he was human.

5
00:00:54,499 --> 00:00:59,880
[Ten years ago, a lonely, radiant winter]

6
00:01:00,747 --> 00:01:04,657
[A goblin enduring eternal life]

7
00:01:07,053 --> 00:01:12,224
[His destined bride, meant to end it]

8
00:01:12,825 --> 00:01:16,930
[A Grim Reaper haunted by a past life]

9
00:01:16,930 --> 00:01:18,898
[And Sunny]

10
00:01:18,898 --> 00:01:20,598
I'm Sunny.

11
00:01:23,536 --> 00:01:28,874
[Bound by fate across time]

12
00:01:29,609 --> 00:01:31,778
[Ten more years pass, and one day]

13
00:01:31,778 --> 00:01:35,114
[On a day that felt just right]

14
00:01:35,114 --> 00:01:37,917
[Their paths begin to cross again...]

15
00:01:41,054 --> 00:01:42,955
Wait a second.

16
00:01:48,595 --> 00:01:54,566
[Eun Tak returns after ten years]

17
00:02:01,641 --> 00:02:06,412
[Mr. Goblin has been summoned too]

18
00:02:06,412 --> 00:02:09,916
I had to pop over to Quebec for a bit.
You know, maple country.

19
00:02:09,916 --> 00:02:12,451
Man, the beef was good.

20
00:02:14,020 --> 00:02:18,858
Hi, I'm Gong Yoo. Ten years ago,

21
00:02:18,858 --> 00:02:22,895
I played Kim Shin in Guardian.

22
00:02:22,895 --> 00:02:25,031
Great to be here.

23
00:02:25,031 --> 00:02:26,232
Hi,

24
00:02:26,232 --> 00:02:29,702
I'm Kim Go Eun. I played Eun Tak in Guardian

25
00:02:29,702 --> 00:02:31,637
ten years ago.

26
00:02:32,639 --> 00:02:34,515
[An immortal goblin in his 949th year]
[The goblin's bride, life after life]

27
00:02:34,515 --> 00:02:36,267
[The Goblin couple, still gorgeous]
Yes.

28
00:02:37,543 --> 00:02:42,248
[Meanwhile, in another dreamlike space...]

29
00:02:42,248 --> 00:02:45,852
- Oh, man.
- Oh, my.

30
00:02:45,852 --> 00:02:47,353
- It's been a while, Sunny.
- It has.

31
00:02:47,353 --> 00:02:50,223
- Have a seat, Mr. Reaper.
- After you. Yes.

32
00:02:50,223 --> 00:02:52,225
- This place feels different.
- It does.

33
00:02:52,225 --> 00:02:54,761
- Familiar, but new.
- Yeah.

34
00:02:54,761 --> 00:02:59,364
How did they even find a place
this close to the afterlife tea room?

35
00:02:59,364 --> 00:03:01,200
- They even have this.
- They do.

36
00:03:01,200 --> 00:03:02,868
[The cup of oblivion]
The ring is here too.

37
00:03:02,868 --> 00:03:04,737
[The jade ring from their past life]
Right. Our rings are here too.

38
00:03:04,737 --> 00:03:07,606
A little late, but once again...

39
00:03:08,708 --> 00:03:10,410
- Oh, it fits?
- It fits perfectly.

40
00:03:10,410 --> 00:03:11,644
- It really does.
- Yes.

41
00:03:11,644 --> 00:03:13,913
[The jade ring finds its owner at last]
This one's definitely mine.

42
00:03:13,913 --> 00:03:19,419
Hi, I'm Yoo In Na. I played Sunny in Guardian.

43
00:03:19,419 --> 00:03:24,390
Hi, I'm Lee Dong Wook.
I played the Grim Reaper.

44
00:03:24,390 --> 00:03:25,958
This feels so surreal.

45
00:03:25,958 --> 00:03:27,827
I mean, "I played Sunny."

46
00:03:27,827 --> 00:03:29,328
- "I played the Grim Reaper."
- "Played."

47
00:03:29,328 --> 00:03:32,098
How many years has it been since we said that?

48
00:03:32,098 --> 00:03:34,801
Yeah. "Played" just comes out now.

49
00:03:34,801 --> 00:03:36,335
[Back in this world, strange yet familiar]
It really is all past tense now, isn't it?

50
00:03:36,335 --> 00:03:38,371
- Ten years have gone by.
- They have.

51
00:03:38,371 --> 00:03:41,474
Over the past ten years,

52
00:03:41,474 --> 00:03:44,911
so many people around me have told me

53
00:03:44,911 --> 00:03:48,281
that Guardian still comes up

54
00:03:48,281 --> 00:03:54,187
and that winter always makes them
think of the show.

55
00:03:54,187 --> 00:03:57,090
To me, it still feels

56
00:03:57,090 --> 00:04:02,061
like the most radiant winter of my life.

57
00:04:02,061 --> 00:04:05,832
You know how you can

58
00:04:05,832 --> 00:04:10,436
pin your most important chats
or notes at the top?

59
00:04:10,436 --> 00:04:13,339
That's what this show

60
00:04:13,339 --> 00:04:15,641
[What Guardian means to In Na]
feels like to me.

61
00:04:15,641 --> 00:04:19,545
It's pinned right at the top

62
00:04:19,545 --> 00:04:22,315
- of my heart.
- Exactly.

63
00:04:22,315 --> 00:04:24,517
[How have the cast stayed in touch?]

64
00:04:24,517 --> 00:04:25,964
We meet up last-minute a lot.

65
00:04:25,964 --> 00:04:28,521
[The Guardian crew loves a last-minute meetup]
Planning things way ahead...

66
00:04:28,521 --> 00:04:30,022
[J for planners, P for spontaneous types]
That's way too J for me.

67
00:04:30,022 --> 00:04:31,624
I'm just not built for that.

68
00:04:31,624 --> 00:04:34,427
[Spontaneous P energy wins again]
So we usually get together on the fly.

69
00:04:34,427 --> 00:04:38,264
And since the three of them
have all been doing this longer than me...

70
00:04:38,264 --> 00:04:39,765
[Unbelievable]

71
00:04:42,168 --> 00:04:45,150
Sorry. I couldn't help it.

72
00:04:45,150 --> 00:04:46,572
- My ego just kicked in.
- Can I finish?

73
00:04:46,572 --> 00:04:48,708
- Just a little?
- I'm sorry.

74
00:04:48,708 --> 00:04:53,479
That's why I feel
like I can just be open with them.

75
00:04:53,479 --> 00:04:55,248
There is a bit of an age gap between us.

76
00:04:55,248 --> 00:04:57,817
But we don't really think about that.
We just feel like friends.

77
00:04:57,817 --> 00:04:59,786
[The four of them are basically friends]
That's how we've stayed close.

78
00:04:59,786 --> 00:05:04,157
Honestly, Dong Wook reaches out
less than Go Eun does.

79
00:05:04,157 --> 00:05:06,526
And yet you two see each other the most!

80
00:05:06,526 --> 00:05:09,061
[Awkward]
And they only go to the nice places together!

81
00:05:09,061 --> 00:05:12,498
[Defending himself]
Sometimes it's just easier with the guys.

82
00:05:12,498 --> 00:05:14,266
So he says.

83
00:05:15,134 --> 00:05:17,303
[How did the 10th anniversary trip begin?]

84
00:05:17,303 --> 00:05:20,206
Someone brought up
that next year would be the 10th anniversary.

85
00:05:20,206 --> 00:05:24,744
So we thought, "Why don't we
do something fun for the anniversary?"

86
00:05:24,744 --> 00:05:27,747
Go Eun was actually the first one to say

87
00:05:27,747 --> 00:05:29,849
she wanted us to do
something for the 10th anniversary.

88
00:05:29,849 --> 00:05:31,117
- I said it a lot!
- Yeah.

89
00:05:31,117 --> 00:05:35,154
When the four of us get together,
we just have this chemistry.

90
00:05:35,154 --> 00:05:40,026
But we never really had a chance
to show people that side of us.

91
00:05:40,026 --> 00:05:42,862
So basically, you wanted to announce
to the world that we're idiots.

92
00:05:42,862 --> 00:05:43,863
No.

93
00:05:43,863 --> 00:05:46,699
Why? Did that hit a nerve?

94
00:05:46,699 --> 00:05:49,068
I didn't even say anything.

95
00:05:49,068 --> 00:05:54,340
I wanted to capture our bond.
It felt too good not to share.

96
00:05:54,340 --> 00:05:56,909
I thought, "The four of us
running around in the sun?

97
00:05:56,909 --> 00:05:59,078
That would be so much fun."

98
00:05:59,078 --> 00:06:01,280
- I was really excited.
- Right.

99
00:06:01,280 --> 00:06:03,248
I'm not getting my hopes up too much.

100
00:06:03,983 --> 00:06:06,285
I just hope we don't fight.

101
00:06:07,053 --> 00:06:10,256
And In Na and Go Eun will

102
00:06:10,256 --> 00:06:13,992
probably spend the whole time
teasing Goblin and me.

103
00:06:14,694 --> 00:06:16,662
As always.

104
00:06:16,662 --> 00:06:18,657
[A preview of the teasing]
You have to do this before we can go.

105
00:06:18,657 --> 00:06:19,665
What is this?

106
00:06:19,665 --> 00:06:22,268
This is just a camera cover.

107
00:06:22,268 --> 00:06:25,204
- When he first sees people, he gets so awkward.
- So awkward.

108
00:06:25,204 --> 00:06:26,072
"Hello"

109
00:06:26,072 --> 00:06:28,241
[Triggered]
I'm not that bad, seriously.

110
00:06:28,241 --> 00:06:30,876
You're trying to bury me here!

111
00:06:34,680 --> 00:06:36,549
[Eyeing his clothes]
This is so cute.

112
00:06:36,549 --> 00:06:40,136
- Why are you pulling out all my clothes?
- Because your clothes are cute.

113
00:06:40,136 --> 00:06:42,922
[The older brothers are overwhelmed]
Okay, you two, enough.

114
00:06:42,922 --> 00:06:44,357
You're driving me nuts.

115
00:06:44,357 --> 00:06:46,559
[Teasing dance]
Eun Tak.

116
00:06:46,559 --> 00:06:49,295
I'm seriously annoyed.

117
00:06:49,295 --> 00:06:51,396
[This is going to be seriously fun]
I'm seriously annoyed.

118
00:06:53,165 --> 00:06:55,167
It'll be chaos, obviously.

119
00:06:57,937 --> 00:06:59,638
Can you see how I feel?

120
00:07:00,406 --> 00:07:02,208
- Everyone will talk over each other.
- You see it, right?

121
00:07:02,208 --> 00:07:03,442
I guess we can already see how this is going.

122
00:07:03,442 --> 00:07:05,045
Yeah. I think everyone will
just say whatever they want.

123
00:07:05,045 --> 00:07:06,112
You nailed it.

124
00:07:06,112 --> 00:07:08,180
Honestly, it'll probably be a mess.

125
00:07:08,180 --> 00:07:10,182
[Guardian's chaotic 10th anniversary trip]
That's what I'm expecting.

126
00:07:10,182 --> 00:07:12,285
No doubt.

127
00:07:12,285 --> 00:07:16,483
[10th anniversary trip, D-7]

128
00:07:17,523 --> 00:07:19,525
[Inside an empty restaurant]

129
00:07:19,525 --> 00:07:22,929
[Gong Yoo arrives first]

130
00:07:22,929 --> 00:07:24,897
[Planner mode: Gong Yoo calls the crew in]
It's 7:30.

131
00:07:24,897 --> 00:07:27,633
Why is no one here?

132
00:07:27,633 --> 00:07:29,635
The oldest one...

133
00:07:30,236 --> 00:07:32,871
got here first and is waiting.

134
00:07:36,075 --> 00:07:38,143
Why are you laughing?

135
00:07:39,211 --> 00:07:41,414
[The goblin's bride arrives]
Why are you laughing?

136
00:07:41,414 --> 00:07:42,715
You came straight from work.

137
00:07:42,715 --> 00:07:43,950
Yeah. I had a press event today.

138
00:07:43,950 --> 00:07:47,486
That video came out today?

139
00:07:47,486 --> 00:07:49,055
You're still dressed exactly like that.

140
00:07:49,055 --> 00:07:51,324
[Go Eun comes straight
from the Yumi's Cells 3 press event]

141
00:07:51,324 --> 00:07:53,492
You had the press event today,

142
00:07:53,492 --> 00:07:55,027
so you figured,

143
00:07:55,027 --> 00:07:56,762
"I'm already all done up. Might as well go."

144
00:07:56,762 --> 00:07:59,165
No, I was going to take my makeup off first.

145
00:07:59,165 --> 00:08:01,733
My manager told me not to.

146
00:08:03,178 --> 00:08:05,705
I came straight
from working out with no makeup on!

147
00:08:05,705 --> 00:08:06,906
Yeah, you look great, though.

148
00:08:06,906 --> 00:08:09,475
I've been taking some time off lately...

149
00:08:09,475 --> 00:08:11,155
[Immortal looks, 949 years strong]
I haven't really been wearing makeup either.

150
00:08:11,155 --> 00:08:13,946
- I look better, right?
- Way better.

151
00:08:13,946 --> 00:08:15,181
I'm hungry.

152
00:08:15,181 --> 00:08:17,416
Should we order first, then?

153
00:08:17,416 --> 00:08:19,663
[Right on cue, the next member arrives]

154
00:08:27,460 --> 00:08:28,594
Hey!

155
00:08:28,594 --> 00:08:30,229
[Sunny arrives with a cute little squeal]

156
00:08:30,229 --> 00:08:31,697
Huh?

157
00:08:31,697 --> 00:08:33,366
- How have you been?
- Hey.

158
00:08:33,366 --> 00:08:34,667
It's been a while.

159
00:08:34,667 --> 00:08:35,768
- How have you been?
- Hey.

160
00:08:35,768 --> 00:08:37,370
[Past-life siblings, reunite]
Yeah. Have you been good?

161
00:08:37,370 --> 00:08:39,271
- Here we are again.
- I know.

162
00:08:39,271 --> 00:08:41,841
- You look gorgeous as ever.
- Stop it.

163
00:08:41,841 --> 00:08:43,743
[Chicken shop reunion]
You had that thing today, right?

164
00:08:43,743 --> 00:08:45,945
- Yeah, the press event.
- I saw you had the press event.

165
00:08:45,945 --> 00:08:47,446
You must be tired.

166
00:08:47,446 --> 00:08:49,348
[Dong Wook is booked today]
She says she needs a post-work drink.

167
00:08:49,348 --> 00:08:50,883
- Right.
- Yeah.

168
00:08:50,883 --> 00:08:52,151
Can I start eating?

169
00:08:52,151 --> 00:08:54,248
Yeah. Why are you asking me?

170
00:08:54,248 --> 00:08:55,299
Still...

171
00:08:55,299 --> 00:08:57,262
- The grown-up hasn't even started yet.
- Why ask me?

172
00:08:57,262 --> 00:08:58,924
What are you talking about?

173
00:08:58,924 --> 00:09:00,276
Just do what you always do.

174
00:09:00,276 --> 00:09:02,873
The grown-ups haven't started,
so the baby can't just go first.

175
00:09:02,873 --> 00:09:06,199
Listen to you acting all proper.

176
00:09:06,199 --> 00:09:07,767
Then I'll go ahead.

177
00:09:07,767 --> 00:09:09,602
- Come on.
- Please, eat up.

178
00:09:09,602 --> 00:09:11,270
[Cute]

179
00:09:11,270 --> 00:09:13,305
I have to say, I'm so happy to be here.

180
00:09:13,305 --> 00:09:15,207
- It feels like it's been forever.
- Because...

181
00:09:15,207 --> 00:09:16,876
- Right.
- Because today...

182
00:09:16,876 --> 00:09:20,880
My male co-star is ten years younger than me.

183
00:09:20,880 --> 00:09:22,148
Really?

184
00:09:22,148 --> 00:09:25,017
Now she finally knows
what it's like on the other side.

185
00:09:25,017 --> 00:09:27,586
- After being the baby everyone adored...
- I just love being the baby, so...

186
00:09:27,586 --> 00:09:30,056
- You're used to it, right?
- No, it's who I am.

187
00:09:30,056 --> 00:09:31,624
- Yeah, that's true.
- It is.

188
00:09:31,624 --> 00:09:33,626
- She was born to be the baby.
- Yeah.

189
00:09:33,626 --> 00:09:35,528
- I'm the baby in my family too.
- Eat up.

190
00:09:35,528 --> 00:09:37,630
Honestly, the most...

191
00:09:37,630 --> 00:09:39,732
- annoying type, if we're being honest.
- Her? Why?

192
00:09:39,732 --> 00:09:41,567
Why am I annoying? Don't be annoyed.

193
00:09:41,567 --> 00:09:45,337
She always calls me "sunbae."

194
00:09:45,337 --> 00:09:47,740
She says it, but...

195
00:09:47,740 --> 00:09:50,009
she basically bosses me around.

196
00:09:50,009 --> 00:09:52,511
I hope they bring the grill soon.

197
00:09:52,511 --> 00:09:54,447
- Can I talk? I'm talking here.
- The grill's not here yet?

198
00:09:54,447 --> 00:09:56,949
- We're not even listening.
- I should've had it ready.

199
00:09:56,949 --> 00:09:57,750
- Exactly.
- Yeah.

200
00:09:57,750 --> 00:10:01,353
- You should've had it ready.
- I mean, I did think about getting it ready.

201
00:10:01,353 --> 00:10:03,989
- But you didn't.
- You can do it next time.

202
00:10:03,989 --> 00:10:05,991
Please prep it ahead next time.

203
00:10:05,991 --> 00:10:07,593
Exactly. So why didn't you?

204
00:10:07,593 --> 00:10:09,095
[In Na, not you too...]

205
00:10:09,095 --> 00:10:11,963
It's tough being outnumbered two to one.

206
00:10:13,132 --> 00:10:17,369
[Missing his Grim Reaper backup]

207
00:10:17,369 --> 00:10:20,673
[Good food and better conversation]

208
00:10:20,673 --> 00:10:24,543
So you set up this pre-trip dinner too?

209
00:10:24,543 --> 00:10:26,745
- I just thought, since we...
- You put this together?

210
00:10:26,745 --> 00:10:30,816
When else would we all get to go away together?

211
00:10:30,816 --> 00:10:32,585
- That's true.
- That too.

212
00:10:32,585 --> 00:10:35,187
- All of us together? That never happens.
- It doesn't.

213
00:10:35,187 --> 00:10:38,724
Honestly, it's hard
to make this happen with all of us.

214
00:10:38,724 --> 00:10:40,559
- Our schedules never line up.
- Exactly.

215
00:10:40,559 --> 00:10:42,394
- It's not just a regular meetup.
- I thought

216
00:10:42,394 --> 00:10:44,430
we could meet up, eat something good,

217
00:10:44,430 --> 00:10:46,674
talk things through, and then go on the trip,

218
00:10:46,674 --> 00:10:48,734
- so we'd all feel more comfortable together.
- Right.

219
00:10:48,734 --> 00:10:51,570
Even if we're close and know each other well,

220
00:10:51,570 --> 00:10:53,939
- traveling together is a whole different thing.
- Totally.

221
00:10:53,939 --> 00:10:57,409
- So I thought, you know...
- Let's keep it friendly!

222
00:10:59,445 --> 00:11:02,281
- Seriously, no fighting. You two.
- No fighting.

223
00:11:02,281 --> 00:11:04,850
- I'm so excited.
- Do you know Gangneung well?

224
00:11:04,850 --> 00:11:06,185
I don't know it that well...

225
00:11:06,185 --> 00:11:08,154
[The 10th anniversary trip to Gangneung]
How long does it take?

226
00:11:08,154 --> 00:11:09,421
- Two and a half hours?
- Two hours?

227
00:11:09,421 --> 00:11:11,090
- Two hours?
- It'll probably be quicker than we think.

228
00:11:11,090 --> 00:11:14,660
But the reason we're going to Gangneung
is our filming location!

229
00:11:14,660 --> 00:11:16,829
- Exactly. I've really wanted to go there.
- You should...

230
00:11:16,829 --> 00:11:19,041
[A trip down memory lane, ten years later]
- I've never been there. - That's true.

231
00:11:21,133 --> 00:11:26,272
[The sea that defined Guardian]

232
00:11:26,272 --> 00:11:32,011
[Where their fate first began]

233
00:11:32,711 --> 00:11:36,831
[Where fate had to say goodbye...]

234
00:11:39,118 --> 00:11:44,287
[Jumunjin, where Guardian lives on]

235
00:11:45,400 --> 00:11:47,626
I really want to go there.

236
00:11:47,626 --> 00:11:50,496
So are we all leaving together?

237
00:11:50,496 --> 00:11:53,632
Don't we need to decide that too?
It's up to us, right?

238
00:11:53,632 --> 00:11:55,601
- We don't even know how we're getting there.
- Are we driving ourselves?

239
00:11:55,601 --> 00:11:58,137
Look into it. You're the J.

240
00:11:58,137 --> 00:11:59,705
- Aren't you a J?
- Oh, you're a J?

241
00:11:59,705 --> 00:12:01,240
- Are you a J?
- I'm totally a J,

242
00:12:01,240 --> 00:12:03,275
but on trips, I'm all P.

243
00:12:03,275 --> 00:12:05,444
I wanted to ask what you two wanted to do.

244
00:12:05,444 --> 00:12:06,312
For me...

245
00:12:06,312 --> 00:12:08,714
[Planner mode is on]
Are we starting with driving there ourselves?

246
00:12:08,714 --> 00:12:10,983
I want to stop at a rest area.

247
00:12:10,983 --> 00:12:12,284
That sounds fun.

248
00:12:12,284 --> 00:12:14,553
I want to stop at a rest area.

249
00:12:14,553 --> 00:12:16,822
[Already in road trip mode]
That sounds fun.

250
00:12:16,822 --> 00:12:19,188
[Already tired]

251
00:12:20,893 --> 00:12:24,196
Okay, first... we all take one car.

252
00:12:24,196 --> 00:12:25,831
- And we stop at a rest area.
- Okay.

253
00:12:25,831 --> 00:12:27,099
Then once we get there...

254
00:12:27,099 --> 00:12:28,300
Just this much.

255
00:12:28,300 --> 00:12:30,636
- Are you listening to me?
- Oh, no. I didn't hear you.

256
00:12:30,636 --> 00:12:31,870
What did you say?

257
00:12:31,870 --> 00:12:33,239
What are we having for dinner?

258
00:12:33,239 --> 00:12:34,673
Pork? Beef?

259
00:12:34,673 --> 00:12:36,475
We need to talk all that through.

260
00:12:36,475 --> 00:12:38,010
Then we write it down.

261
00:12:38,010 --> 00:12:40,646
Then we decide what to buy in the car.

262
00:12:40,646 --> 00:12:42,181
- Got it?
- I'll take notes.

263
00:12:42,181 --> 00:12:43,849
Once we get there,
the things you mentioned earlier...

264
00:12:43,849 --> 00:12:45,884
[Full-on trip planning]
we do everything on the list,

265
00:12:45,884 --> 00:12:47,453
- then at the place we're staying...
- This pen is so cute! What is it?

266
00:12:47,453 --> 00:12:49,154
- No, wait.
- I'll give it to you later. Take it.

267
00:12:49,154 --> 00:12:50,556
[Planning is not going well]
No, stay with me.

268
00:12:50,556 --> 00:12:51,724
We keep getting distracted.

269
00:12:51,724 --> 00:12:53,459
- No, but the pen is so...
- Oh, your earrings are so cute!

270
00:12:53,459 --> 00:12:55,060
This pen is so cool! Look at this.

271
00:12:55,060 --> 00:12:57,930
[An immortal goblin slowly losing it]
Look at this. Seriously.

272
00:12:57,930 --> 00:13:00,866
- Do you have this pen?
- Isn't it so cool?

273
00:13:00,866 --> 00:13:02,867
It is cute, though.

274
00:13:03,469 --> 00:13:05,137
I mean, it is cute.

275
00:13:05,137 --> 00:13:06,238
He's such a good sport.

276
00:13:06,238 --> 00:13:08,040
- It's cute.
- He just takes it all.

277
00:13:08,040 --> 00:13:10,909
We could tease him for 100 hours,
and he still wouldn't get mad.

278
00:13:10,909 --> 00:13:12,778
[Sweet Gong Yoo never gets mad]
He just keeps explaining anyway.

279
00:13:12,778 --> 00:13:15,314
Okay, wake up!

280
00:13:15,314 --> 00:13:17,215
Right. He never gets mad.

281
00:13:18,150 --> 00:13:20,352
- As long as you like it.
- Look at his face.

282
00:13:20,352 --> 00:13:22,488
But I was thinking,

283
00:13:22,488 --> 00:13:25,333
we might have guests that night.

284
00:13:25,333 --> 00:13:27,893
Anyone you'd want to invite?

285
00:13:27,893 --> 00:13:30,296
- I'd love for everyone to come.
- I want to see everyone too.

286
00:13:30,296 --> 00:13:31,263
Of course.

287
00:13:31,263 --> 00:13:32,731
The more, the better, right?

288
00:13:32,731 --> 00:13:33,932
[Guardian wrap party]
[Actor Kim Ki Doo, Actor Yoon Kyung Ho]

289
00:13:33,932 --> 00:13:36,368
[Actress Park Kyung Hye,
Actress Kim Seo Jeong]

290
00:13:36,368 --> 00:13:39,104
[Actress Lee El, Actor Choi Woong,
Writer Kim Eun Sook]

291
00:13:39,104 --> 00:13:44,335
[A team bonded by hard work]

292
00:13:44,335 --> 00:13:46,937
- Yoon Kyung Ho.
- Yoon Kyung Ho.

293
00:13:46,937 --> 00:13:48,013
- Yes, him.
- Me too.

294
00:13:48,013 --> 00:13:50,683
- And Kyung Hye, the ghost.
- Yeah.

295
00:13:50,683 --> 00:13:51,917
I'd love to see Kyung Hye too.

296
00:13:51,917 --> 00:13:53,385
- Yeom Hye Ran.
- Yeom Hye Ran.

297
00:13:53,385 --> 00:13:54,720
I hope Yeom Hye Ran can come.

298
00:13:54,720 --> 00:13:56,455
I really miss her.

299
00:13:56,455 --> 00:13:58,424
Jo Woo Jin.

300
00:13:58,424 --> 00:14:00,392
- Jo Woo Jin.
- Who do you think will come?

301
00:14:00,392 --> 00:14:03,395
- Everyone from Guardian is so busy now!
- Right.

302
00:14:03,395 --> 00:14:06,031
Getting everyone together is
kind of impossible, right?

303
00:14:06,031 --> 00:14:09,068
- Sung Jae must be busy too, right?
- Yeah.

304
00:14:09,068 --> 00:14:10,536
I wonder how Sung Jae's doing.

305
00:14:10,536 --> 00:14:12,905
I'd love for writer Kim Eun Sook to come.

306
00:14:12,905 --> 00:14:15,974
Right. It's been way too long since we saw her.

307
00:14:15,974 --> 00:14:20,679
Let's throw a really fun Guardian
10th anniversary party with the guests.

308
00:14:20,679 --> 00:14:22,381
- I like that.
- Make it feel real.

309
00:14:22,381 --> 00:14:24,950
[The four of them together]
Whatever we do, it's our 10th anniversary.

310
00:14:24,950 --> 00:14:27,453
We're getting together for the 10th

311
00:14:27,453 --> 00:14:30,289
and spending over 24 hours together.

312
00:14:30,289 --> 00:14:31,769
This side of us...

313
00:14:31,769 --> 00:14:33,992
- We've never shown people that before.
- Right.

314
00:14:33,992 --> 00:14:39,031
People are probably
wondering if we're still close.

315
00:14:39,031 --> 00:14:41,300
But not this much...

316
00:14:41,300 --> 00:14:46,004
No one knows we're this chaotic together.

317
00:14:46,004 --> 00:14:47,206
It's the ocean!

318
00:14:47,206 --> 00:14:49,274
[Back in Gangneung, ten years later]
Man, imagine if we hadn't come.

319
00:14:49,274 --> 00:14:50,876
[The four we fell for back then]
Say hi to the drone.

320
00:14:50,876 --> 00:14:52,177
Oh, I see the drone.

321
00:14:52,177 --> 00:14:53,412
Happy 10th anniversary!

322
00:14:53,412 --> 00:14:54,980
- Happy anniversary!
- Happy anniversary!

323
00:14:54,980 --> 00:14:56,482
- Let's have a great time today.
- Yes.

324
00:14:56,482 --> 00:14:58,650
Yes, my dear sunbaes.

325
00:15:00,119 --> 00:15:01,587
Tinker Bell.

326
00:15:01,587 --> 00:15:03,322
I just became an adult.

327
00:15:03,322 --> 00:15:05,391
[The baby charm melts them all]

328
00:15:05,391 --> 00:15:07,872
I love being doted on.

329
00:15:08,827 --> 00:15:10,229
[Life as the baby is sweet]
Yeah.

330
00:15:10,229 --> 00:15:11,764
I'm really happy.

331
00:15:11,764 --> 00:15:13,132
[Go Eun was born to be the baby]

332
00:15:13,132 --> 00:15:17,369
I brought soy sauce,
perilla oil, and tuna sauce.

333
00:15:17,369 --> 00:15:18,871
I brought drinks too.

334
00:15:18,871 --> 00:15:20,706
[Next-level prep]
Oh, that's the stew!

335
00:15:20,706 --> 00:15:22,474
He brought marshmallows too.

336
00:15:22,474 --> 00:15:25,644
[Even the meat thickness is planned]
Could you slice it about 1.5 to 2 cm thick?

337
00:15:25,644 --> 00:15:28,013
- Want to take a walk?
- No, we have to cook.

338
00:15:28,013 --> 00:15:30,282
When you're traveling,
having someone like that around...

339
00:15:30,282 --> 00:15:31,750
[Dependable eldest Gong Yoo]
is honestly the best.

340
00:15:31,750 --> 00:15:34,720
[Glowing in the sun]
Oh, I look really pretty from this angle.

341
00:15:34,720 --> 00:15:36,688
[She brings the warmth]

342
00:15:36,688 --> 00:15:37,723
Give it up.

343
00:15:37,723 --> 00:15:39,758
In Na always says things so sweetly.

344
00:15:39,758 --> 00:15:41,360
What a smart baby.

345
00:15:41,360 --> 00:15:43,595
This is such a happy afternoon.

346
00:15:43,595 --> 00:15:45,164
[Warm to everyone]
Let's all do the cute pose.

347
00:15:45,164 --> 00:15:46,832
- What was that?
- Seriously, what was that?

348
00:15:46,832 --> 00:15:47,866
[Pure Sunny energy]
What?

349
00:15:47,866 --> 00:15:49,668
[Yoo In Na, always bringing the warmth]

350
00:15:49,668 --> 00:15:52,504
[Wook is all grumbles]
Man, even the simplest thing is a chore.

351
00:15:52,504 --> 00:15:53,539
Put this on.

352
00:15:53,539 --> 00:15:55,374
[Grumpy, but sweet]
No, I'm not cold.

353
00:15:55,374 --> 00:15:57,342
[He even opens the door]
Yes, I'll get out now.

354
00:15:57,342 --> 00:15:59,044
[He even buys them bags]
I'll pay for this.

355
00:15:59,044 --> 00:16:00,446
- No.
- No, really.

356
00:16:00,446 --> 00:16:02,514
[Dong Wook, the practical big brother]
Come on, it's fine between us.

357
00:16:02,514 --> 00:16:03,949
So sweet.

358
00:16:03,949 --> 00:16:06,151
Get the girls in closer.

359
00:16:06,151 --> 00:16:07,453
And now he's moving into the middle.

360
00:16:07,453 --> 00:16:09,788
[Stopped before getting next to Wook]
No.

361
00:16:09,788 --> 00:16:13,692
Don't we look so happy?
I'm seriously so happy right now.

362
00:16:13,692 --> 00:16:15,427
Man!

363
00:16:15,427 --> 00:16:17,796
Nice!

364
00:16:17,796 --> 00:16:19,598
[Together again after ten years]
Wrong!

365
00:16:19,598 --> 00:16:20,632
Wrong!

366
00:16:20,632 --> 00:16:22,468
[A trip that shines even brighter]

367
00:16:22,468 --> 00:16:24,403
This is the best.

368
00:16:24,403 --> 00:16:25,504
It really is.

369
00:16:25,504 --> 00:16:26,972
Oh, this is so embarrassing. Stop it.

370
00:16:26,972 --> 00:16:30,075
[Guardian's 10th anniversary trip begins]

371
00:16:30,075 --> 00:16:33,453
[10th anniversary trip, D-day]

372
00:16:34,780 --> 00:16:37,549
[8:00 a.m., Olympic Park parking lot]

373
00:16:37,549 --> 00:16:39,251
How am I supposed to carry all this?

374
00:16:39,251 --> 00:16:40,652
Can you carry this?

375
00:16:40,652 --> 00:16:42,221
Why is this so heavy?

376
00:16:42,221 --> 00:16:43,155
It's heavy.

377
00:16:43,155 --> 00:16:44,323
[Huge at first glance]
It really is.

378
00:16:44,323 --> 00:16:46,492
What is this right now?

379
00:16:46,492 --> 00:16:49,294
[Peak J brought the whole fridge]
I ordered and packed the stuff

380
00:16:49,294 --> 00:16:50,562
we couldn't buy at the market.

381
00:16:50,562 --> 00:16:52,297
Good call.

382
00:16:53,065 --> 00:16:56,034
- So I have to keep walking like this?
- Yeah.

383
00:16:56,034 --> 00:16:57,536
[One shoulder taking the hit]

384
00:16:57,536 --> 00:16:59,204
This must be the car.

385
00:16:59,204 --> 00:17:01,974
- Where is it? Where are we going?
- This one.

386
00:17:01,974 --> 00:17:04,376
I think they did this...

387
00:17:04,376 --> 00:17:06,044
on purpose.

388
00:17:06,044 --> 00:17:08,747
- They picked this car on purpose.
- Yeah, exactly. Looks like it.

389
00:17:08,747 --> 00:17:10,282
Right?

390
00:17:10,282 --> 00:17:13,315
[About this car...]

391
00:17:14,686 --> 00:17:16,495
We're here. Get out.

392
00:17:19,091 --> 00:17:23,128
[The car that carried Goblin everywhere]

393
00:17:23,128 --> 00:17:25,363
A thank-you for the maple leaf.

394
00:17:26,064 --> 00:17:30,035
[Ten years later]

395
00:17:30,035 --> 00:17:33,639
[Ready for one more memory trip]

396
00:17:33,639 --> 00:17:36,542
[Mr. Buckwheat joins the ride]

397
00:17:36,542 --> 00:17:38,243
Will all this fit?

398
00:17:38,243 --> 00:17:39,978
This...

399
00:17:40,879 --> 00:17:44,917
[Ten years later, even the controls are fuzzy]

400
00:17:44,917 --> 00:17:46,538
It won't open?

401
00:17:47,386 --> 00:17:50,055
[How did this work again?]

402
00:17:50,055 --> 00:17:51,523
[Click]

403
00:17:51,523 --> 00:17:52,958
[First memory unlocked, ten years later]

404
00:17:52,958 --> 00:17:55,394
Yeah, it'll fit.

405
00:17:55,394 --> 00:17:57,296
This should go in upright, right?

406
00:17:57,296 --> 00:17:58,497
It shouldn't lie flat, right?

407
00:17:58,497 --> 00:18:00,866
Then let's put this here.

408
00:18:00,866 --> 00:18:01,833
- Like this.
- And then...

409
00:18:01,833 --> 00:18:02,980
We need to keep it from moving.

410
00:18:02,980 --> 00:18:05,771
The others will have bags too.

411
00:18:05,771 --> 00:18:07,372
Leave this open. Why aren't they here?

412
00:18:07,372 --> 00:18:09,508
[Where are In Na and Go Eun?]
No idea.

413
00:18:09,508 --> 00:18:11,566
[Go Eun arrives half-awake]

414
00:18:11,566 --> 00:18:13,312
- She looks...
- You want some help?

415
00:18:13,312 --> 00:18:15,814
Come here. Hurry up.

416
00:18:15,814 --> 00:18:17,649
- No, I'm okay.
- Can you make it over here?

417
00:18:17,649 --> 00:18:19,661
[Answering himself]
Yeah. Come here.

418
00:18:23,822 --> 00:18:26,257
Then why did you even ask?

419
00:18:27,025 --> 00:18:28,727
[Arms wide open]
Is it heavy?

420
00:18:28,727 --> 00:18:30,762
Can we say hi first?

421
00:18:31,930 --> 00:18:33,565
- Have you been well?
- Yeah.

422
00:18:33,565 --> 00:18:34,866
[Always bickering, always happy to meet]

423
00:18:34,866 --> 00:18:38,270
- Can you just carry the kimchi?
- Got it.

424
00:18:38,270 --> 00:18:39,404
[Grumbles, but gets it done]

425
00:18:39,404 --> 00:18:41,773
Hello.

426
00:18:41,773 --> 00:18:42,608
[Making room for the baby]

427
00:18:42,608 --> 00:18:45,077
- Your suitcase should go on top.
- How?

428
00:18:45,077 --> 00:18:46,345
Huh?

429
00:18:46,345 --> 00:18:49,414
How much are you planning to eat
that you brought kimchi too?

430
00:18:49,414 --> 00:18:51,449
They told me to bring kimchi.

431
00:18:52,351 --> 00:18:54,686
I'm a little worried about the kimchi.

432
00:18:54,686 --> 00:18:57,956
Why are you worried about the kimchi?
My mom packed this really well.

433
00:18:57,956 --> 00:19:00,058
- Are you saying my mom can't pack?
- No.

434
00:19:00,058 --> 00:19:02,394
[Panicking]
I'm worried it'll slide around in there.

435
00:19:02,394 --> 00:19:04,930
What is he still doing?

436
00:19:04,930 --> 00:19:08,667
[Locked in]
Just let him do what he wants.

437
00:19:08,667 --> 00:19:10,702
I'm still worried about the kimchi.

438
00:19:10,702 --> 00:19:12,004
What should I do with it?

439
00:19:12,004 --> 00:19:14,940
[Goblin is deep in trunk Tetris]

440
00:19:14,940 --> 00:19:17,241
It feels like it'll spill.

441
00:19:19,978 --> 00:19:21,113
Should we go ahead?

442
00:19:21,113 --> 00:19:22,700
- Go without her?
- Are you done now?

443
00:19:22,700 --> 00:19:25,535
- Should we leave her to catch up?
- Close it.

444
00:19:27,719 --> 00:19:28,754
Hi.

445
00:19:28,754 --> 00:19:30,555
[In Na arrives with a huge suitcase]

446
00:19:31,491 --> 00:19:34,426
- Wait, don't bring luggage...
- The luggage...

447
00:19:34,426 --> 00:19:35,727
- Hi.
- Hey.

448
00:19:35,727 --> 00:19:37,663
[Wook, the bag carrier, is back]
Load it up.

449
00:19:37,663 --> 00:19:39,765
- Did you come over to carry this for me?
- Yeah.

450
00:19:39,765 --> 00:19:42,434
- But...
- Yeah?

451
00:19:42,434 --> 00:19:44,269
Why did you pack so much food?

452
00:19:44,269 --> 00:19:45,971
Why do you assume it's food?

453
00:19:45,971 --> 00:19:48,440
- Isn't it food?
- It is.

454
00:19:48,440 --> 00:19:50,275
[Welcome]
Hey.

455
00:19:50,275 --> 00:19:51,943
Go Eun.

456
00:19:51,943 --> 00:19:53,445
Wait, weren't you bringing coffee?

457
00:19:53,445 --> 00:19:54,646
- Coffee?
- Yeah.

458
00:19:54,646 --> 00:19:57,149
What is this?

459
00:19:57,149 --> 00:19:58,784
- What about it?
- What's with the tumbler?

460
00:19:58,784 --> 00:20:00,551
[In Na even brought coffee for the day]
They're gifts.

461
00:20:01,820 --> 00:20:03,288
- I think it'll fit.
- Yeah.

462
00:20:03,288 --> 00:20:04,189
[Trunk Tetris, final final round]

463
00:20:04,189 --> 00:20:06,791
- Can't we lay it down?
- No, I think we can keep it upright.

464
00:20:07,693 --> 00:20:11,063
- We got it.
- We got it.

465
00:20:11,063 --> 00:20:13,031
[Already exhausted]
Go on without me.

466
00:20:13,031 --> 00:20:14,332
It's been real.

467
00:20:14,332 --> 00:20:16,368
[Someone's already opting out]
Have a good trip.

468
00:20:16,368 --> 00:20:20,571
[After that brutal Trunk Tetris]
All right, then.

469
00:20:21,173 --> 00:20:23,642
Oh, this is so cute.

470
00:20:23,642 --> 00:20:26,645
[The whole crew is finally ready]

471
00:20:26,645 --> 00:20:28,258
There's no fine dust today.

472
00:20:28,258 --> 00:20:29,648
- The weather's perfect.
- I know.

473
00:20:29,648 --> 00:20:31,383
- It's the nicest it's been in a while.
- Really?

474
00:20:31,383 --> 00:20:34,018
[Off to Gangneung]
Yeah, the air quality's good today.

475
00:20:34,886 --> 00:20:37,334
[Seoul, Rest Stop, Jumunjin]

476
00:20:37,334 --> 00:20:40,092
[About two and a half hours to Gangneung]

477
00:20:40,092 --> 00:20:43,762
[The Goblin crew's first trip in ten years]

478
00:20:43,762 --> 00:20:46,231
Hurry, look at the weather.

479
00:20:46,231 --> 00:20:48,633
- Look over to the right.
- The weather is so nice.

480
00:20:48,633 --> 00:20:50,202
[Even the weather is celebrating]

481
00:20:50,202 --> 00:20:53,822
I brought something
for our hangovers tomorrow morning.

482
00:20:53,822 --> 00:20:54,873
What?

483
00:20:54,873 --> 00:20:57,008
[Gong Yoo's master food plan]
So... There's this...

484
00:20:57,008 --> 00:20:58,543
gomtang place I go to a lot.

485
00:20:58,543 --> 00:20:59,857
[Gomtang from his go-to spot]
They sell it frozen.

486
00:20:59,857 --> 00:21:01,713
- It comes as a meal kit.
- Yeah.

487
00:21:01,713 --> 00:21:04,449
I sliced scallions for the gomtang.

488
00:21:04,449 --> 00:21:05,417
- What?
- Nice.

489
00:21:05,417 --> 00:21:06,818
[She even sliced the scallions?]
Why did you bring scallions too?

490
00:21:06,818 --> 00:21:09,254
No, here's why.

491
00:21:09,254 --> 00:21:11,256
- Scallions go in everything.
- Right.

492
00:21:11,256 --> 00:21:13,125
But slicing them makes you cry.

493
00:21:13,125 --> 00:21:15,727
- So you sliced them ahead of time?
- I put on goggles and sliced them.

494
00:21:15,727 --> 00:21:18,964
I figured we could use them for something,
so I packed them.

495
00:21:18,964 --> 00:21:20,732
Look at us.

496
00:21:20,732 --> 00:21:22,834
- That worked out great.
- We're totally on the same page.

497
00:21:22,834 --> 00:21:24,469
I mean, basically...

498
00:21:24,469 --> 00:21:27,839
If we have that many scallions ready,
we'll use them in everything.

499
00:21:27,839 --> 00:21:29,641
- We'll use them in everything.
- Of course.

500
00:21:29,641 --> 00:21:31,409
We did good. Kimchi and scallions...

501
00:21:31,409 --> 00:21:33,044
- We're so proud of ourselves.
- Yeah, we're good.

502
00:21:33,044 --> 00:21:34,546
- I did good, right?
- You did.

503
00:21:34,546 --> 00:21:36,314
- I wasn't sure we'd even use the scallions.
- How do you...

504
00:21:36,314 --> 00:21:38,250
How do you even think of that?

505
00:21:38,250 --> 00:21:40,519
[Big brother did good too]

506
00:21:40,519 --> 00:21:43,455
[Checking out what In Na packed]
You're seriously amazing.

507
00:21:43,455 --> 00:21:45,590
[Household pro In Na's list]
Salt. Perilla powder. Sugar.

508
00:21:45,590 --> 00:21:47,492
Ground sesame seeds. Chili flakes.

509
00:21:47,492 --> 00:21:49,361
- Minced garlic.
- This is the best part.

510
00:21:49,361 --> 00:21:51,797
[She even ground the sesame herself]
I ground it myself, and now it looks like this.

511
00:21:51,797 --> 00:21:53,331
[All kinds of seasonings]
Good call.

512
00:21:53,331 --> 00:21:56,101
[Sliced onions, Sliced scallions,
Scallions, Fruit]

513
00:21:56,101 --> 00:21:58,603
[Goggles for onion-level tears]

514
00:21:58,603 --> 00:22:03,975
I brought soy sauce, perilla oil,
and tuna sauce.

515
00:22:03,975 --> 00:22:06,311
- Then you brought exactly what I didn't.
- Exactly.

516
00:22:06,311 --> 00:22:08,513
- You brought everything we still needed.
- Perilla oil, tuna sauce,

517
00:22:08,513 --> 00:22:10,148
- and soy sauce.
- You guys are seriously...

518
00:22:10,148 --> 00:22:12,584
Let's lay everything out once we get there.

519
00:22:12,584 --> 00:22:14,552
[The 10th anniversary feast
is already promising]

520
00:22:18,023 --> 00:22:20,091
- What? Are you sleepy?
- No.

521
00:22:20,091 --> 00:22:22,994
20 minutes in the car,
and she's already yawning like a baby.

522
00:22:22,994 --> 00:22:24,830
How is she yawning that hard already?

523
00:22:24,830 --> 00:22:26,631
[Hehe]

524
00:22:26,631 --> 00:22:29,601
I love this.
I love being treated like the baby here.

525
00:22:29,601 --> 00:22:31,436
- I'm so happy.
- You are the baby.

526
00:22:31,436 --> 00:22:33,071
- You're the baby here.
- Yes!

527
00:22:33,071 --> 00:22:34,631
- You'll always be the baby.
- Right.

528
00:22:34,631 --> 00:22:35,831
What baby?

529
00:22:35,831 --> 00:22:38,276
- Come on, she is the baby.
- Oh, be quiet.

530
00:22:38,276 --> 00:22:40,378
- She's not exactly a baby anymore.
- You haven't seen me in forever.

531
00:22:40,378 --> 00:22:42,180
You were a baby back when we shot Guardian.

532
00:22:42,180 --> 00:22:44,983
- In Na says I am, though.
- That's right.

533
00:22:44,983 --> 00:22:48,420
- Go Eun is... what, this year?
- Who said I needed your approval?

534
00:22:48,420 --> 00:22:51,656
- Did I ask?
- Did you just turn 21 this year?

535
00:22:52,624 --> 00:22:54,893
[There he goes again]
That attitude, though.

536
00:22:54,893 --> 00:22:57,529
Was she 11 when we shot Guardian?

537
00:22:57,529 --> 00:22:59,931
Here, eat this.

538
00:22:59,931 --> 00:23:01,666
[In Na distracts him with fruit]
And In Na just turned 28.

539
00:23:01,666 --> 00:23:02,934
- Hey, that one.
- Yeah?

540
00:23:02,934 --> 00:23:04,269
Give Goblin some too.

541
00:23:04,269 --> 00:23:06,304
- How's that cherry tomato?
- It's good.

542
00:23:06,304 --> 00:23:07,973
- It's good.
- It's really good, right?

543
00:23:07,973 --> 00:23:08,974
- It's good.
- Grapes?

544
00:23:08,974 --> 00:23:10,709
Have a cherry tomato,

545
00:23:10,709 --> 00:23:12,777
then some blueberries.

546
00:23:12,777 --> 00:23:15,614
[Everyone's feeding each other]

547
00:23:15,614 --> 00:23:16,781
[Mmm]
So good, right?

548
00:23:16,781 --> 00:23:18,149
And also,

549
00:23:18,149 --> 00:23:21,152
you guys always eat nuts.

550
00:23:21,152 --> 00:23:22,654
So I brought some nuts too.

551
00:23:22,654 --> 00:23:24,589
You really are the best.

552
00:23:24,589 --> 00:23:26,157
[In Na packed everyone's favorites]

553
00:23:26,157 --> 00:23:27,959
I even brought gummies

554
00:23:27,959 --> 00:23:30,428
for him in case he gets cranky later.

555
00:23:30,428 --> 00:23:32,230
He loves gummies.

556
00:23:32,230 --> 00:23:34,199
Yeah, I love gummies.

557
00:23:34,199 --> 00:23:36,101
Every gummy in the world...

558
00:23:36,101 --> 00:23:39,738
- He eats every gummy he can find.
- Yeah, that's true.

559
00:23:39,738 --> 00:23:41,506
You're all so prepared.

560
00:23:41,506 --> 00:23:44,075
You brought snacks, groceries, everything.

561
00:23:44,075 --> 00:23:47,311
- I literally just brought my phone.
- Good job.

562
00:23:48,546 --> 00:23:50,093
Wait, you said 90 kilometers earlier,

563
00:23:50,093 --> 00:23:52,303
and now we only have 70 left?

564
00:23:52,303 --> 00:23:53,084
Yeah.

565
00:23:53,084 --> 00:23:57,188
So three more of those, and we're there?

566
00:23:57,188 --> 00:23:58,626
Yeah.

567
00:23:59,259 --> 00:24:01,726
I'm having so much fun already.

568
00:24:01,726 --> 00:24:03,561
Yeah.

569
00:24:03,561 --> 00:24:05,497
What a shame.

570
00:24:05,497 --> 00:24:06,665
[Where did his soul go?]
What? What did he say?

571
00:24:06,665 --> 00:24:07,899
He said, "What a shame."

572
00:24:07,899 --> 00:24:10,635
The least sad person alive just said he's sad.

573
00:24:10,635 --> 00:24:12,436
[That's peak T energy from Dong Wook]

574
00:24:13,200 --> 00:24:14,205
Want to stop for a bit?

575
00:24:14,205 --> 00:24:15,540
Let's pull in.

576
00:24:15,540 --> 00:24:16,753
- Let's pull in.
- Oh, this is it.

577
00:24:16,753 --> 00:24:18,776
[They laugh their way to the rest stop]
It's Munmak Rest Stop.

578
00:24:19,778 --> 00:24:20,946
In Na, put these on now.

579
00:24:20,946 --> 00:24:22,180
- No, I'm okay.
- No.

580
00:24:22,180 --> 00:24:24,616
- You're going outside.
- I'll give them back when you drive again.

581
00:24:24,616 --> 00:24:26,017
[Sweet Peach Couple moment]

582
00:24:26,017 --> 00:24:28,086
- You didn't bring sunglasses?
- No.

583
00:24:28,086 --> 00:24:30,255
[Everyone gets out, excited for snacks]

584
00:24:30,255 --> 00:24:33,344
[Why isn't In Na getting out?]

585
00:24:34,759 --> 00:24:36,747
[Struggling]

586
00:24:41,566 --> 00:24:43,535
In Na, if you open the door all the way,

587
00:24:43,535 --> 00:24:45,203
you can get out so much easier.

588
00:24:45,203 --> 00:24:46,738
Why are you only opening it this much?

589
00:24:46,738 --> 00:24:48,707
Try it again. Do it again.

590
00:24:48,707 --> 00:24:49,908
- Do it again.
- Hey.

591
00:24:49,908 --> 00:24:51,388
I'll start over.

592
00:24:51,388 --> 00:24:53,812
See, In Na? If you open the door like this,

593
00:24:53,812 --> 00:24:55,613
it's much easier to get out.

594
00:24:55,613 --> 00:24:57,282
Why squeeze out

595
00:24:57,282 --> 00:24:59,050
- through that tiny gap?
- I was just...

596
00:24:59,050 --> 00:25:00,285
- You were all, "Oof," trying to get out.
- Like this.

597
00:25:00,285 --> 00:25:02,667
[Lecturing her while opening the door]

598
00:25:02,667 --> 00:25:03,738
Where are we going?

599
00:25:03,738 --> 00:25:04,989
Right here. This way.

600
00:25:04,989 --> 00:25:07,492
[Off to get snacks]

601
00:25:07,492 --> 00:25:08,994
[A little waist squeeze]

602
00:25:08,994 --> 00:25:11,496
Look at this tiny waist.

603
00:25:11,496 --> 00:25:12,764
Oh, come on.

604
00:25:12,764 --> 00:25:14,632
You know...

605
00:25:14,632 --> 00:25:16,301
Dating you would be amazing.

606
00:25:16,301 --> 00:25:17,836
Because my waist is this tiny?

607
00:25:17,836 --> 00:25:20,171
- It's so satisfying...
- I think dating you would be amazing too.

608
00:25:20,171 --> 00:25:22,507
- It's so satisfying to hold.
- You'd be so much fun to date.

609
00:25:22,507 --> 00:25:23,408
No, I wouldn't.

610
00:25:23,408 --> 00:25:26,978
- You're cuter than a puppy.
- I might not act cute at all.

611
00:25:26,978 --> 00:25:29,080
- I'd just mess with you.
- That's the charm.

612
00:25:29,080 --> 00:25:32,211
[Still close after ten years]
Even bickering with you would be fun.

613
00:25:32,977 --> 00:25:34,652
[First rest-stop snack: fish cake]
What should we get?

614
00:25:34,652 --> 00:25:36,788
- What flavor do you want?
- Samjin Fish Cake is good.

615
00:25:36,788 --> 00:25:38,233
- Yeah, I did...
- I'll get squid.

616
00:25:38,233 --> 00:25:39,257
Spicy pepper.

617
00:25:39,257 --> 00:25:40,125
She wants spicy pepper.

618
00:25:40,125 --> 00:25:41,726
- Two spicy ones.
- Two spicy peppers.

619
00:25:41,726 --> 00:25:43,461
- One squid.
- One squid.

620
00:25:43,461 --> 00:25:44,529
I want squid too.

621
00:25:44,529 --> 00:25:46,531
[Spicy: two, Squid: two]
Two squid.

622
00:25:46,531 --> 00:25:48,033
Samjin Fish Cake bars.

623
00:25:48,033 --> 00:25:49,601
- Look.
- Need anything else?

624
00:25:49,601 --> 00:25:51,603
Huh? They have kiosks here too?

625
00:25:51,603 --> 00:25:54,305
I brought cash.

626
00:25:56,041 --> 00:25:57,675
- Don't make yourself look old.
- Checkout.

627
00:25:57,675 --> 00:25:59,110
You can't even pay cash.

628
00:25:59,110 --> 00:26:01,146
- Card payment.
- Cash isn't even an option.

629
00:26:01,146 --> 00:26:03,948
- It's a kiosk.
- Look at you go.

630
00:26:03,948 --> 00:26:05,550
I carry cash too sometimes.

631
00:26:05,550 --> 00:26:09,199
- I haven't seen someone carry cash in forever.
- I brought it because I wanted to buy Go Eun

632
00:26:09,199 --> 00:26:12,590
[Cash ready to treat the youngest]
something good at the rest stop.

633
00:26:12,590 --> 00:26:14,726
Oh, it's already ready. Which one is which?

634
00:26:14,726 --> 00:26:18,196
- Two squid ones.
- I guess you don't put anything on this.

635
00:26:18,196 --> 00:26:20,165
You can grab the sauces from the fridge.

636
00:26:20,165 --> 00:26:21,800
She says the sauces are in the fridge.

637
00:26:21,800 --> 00:26:22,767
You got this one too?

638
00:26:22,767 --> 00:26:24,002
- Yeah.
- Me too.

639
00:26:24,002 --> 00:26:25,703
[Sharing the sauce, too]

640
00:26:25,703 --> 00:26:28,039
- Let's get back in the car.
- Are we getting back?

641
00:26:28,039 --> 00:26:30,809
But I still want more.

642
00:26:30,809 --> 00:26:31,976
- You want more?
- Yes.

643
00:26:31,976 --> 00:26:33,511
No. We'll eat when we get there.

644
00:26:33,511 --> 00:26:35,180
- I need something sweet too.
- Then get something sweet.

645
00:26:35,180 --> 00:26:36,381
Something sweet.

646
00:26:36,381 --> 00:26:37,715
They have walnut cakes here.

647
00:26:37,715 --> 00:26:38,883
[Next up, sweet walnut cakes]
Huh?

648
00:26:38,883 --> 00:26:40,670
- Then walnut cakes it is.
- The walnut cakes will take

649
00:26:40,670 --> 00:26:41,719
about three minutes.

650
00:26:41,719 --> 00:26:42,801
- It's spicy.
- Three minutes?

651
00:26:42,801 --> 00:26:44,122
- Three to four minutes.
- Okay.

652
00:26:44,122 --> 00:26:46,124
He said it'll take three or four minutes.

653
00:26:46,124 --> 00:26:48,393
- That's okay, right?
- Then we'll wait. Sit down.

654
00:26:48,393 --> 00:26:51,229
[Waiting with fish cakes in hand]

655
00:26:51,229 --> 00:26:53,231
- Want to try this?
- Want to trade?

656
00:26:53,231 --> 00:26:55,166
Trade? Like, the whole thing?

657
00:26:55,166 --> 00:26:56,768
[The Goblin couple shares a bite]
Are you sure?

658
00:26:56,768 --> 00:26:58,770
What is that one? Who got the spicy one?

659
00:26:58,770 --> 00:27:01,039
- Me.
- Eun Tak got the spicy one.

660
00:27:01,039 --> 00:27:03,074
[Trading bites]

661
00:27:03,074 --> 00:27:05,043
I...

662
00:27:05,043 --> 00:27:07,512
- At a rest stop...
- This is good.

663
00:27:07,512 --> 00:27:09,247
- Sitting down like this to eat.
- Eating outside...

664
00:27:09,247 --> 00:27:10,715
- like this.
- This is pretty much our first time, right?

665
00:27:10,715 --> 00:27:13,751
- Yeah. We don't really get to do this.
- It's been decades.

666
00:27:13,751 --> 00:27:15,820
- Eating outside at a rest stop.
- Yeah.

667
00:27:15,820 --> 00:27:18,823
[Same here]

668
00:27:18,823 --> 00:27:20,024
[Even the ordinary feels new together]

669
00:27:20,024 --> 00:27:21,926
- Is it good?
- There really aren't that many people.

670
00:27:21,926 --> 00:27:25,130
I thought it'd be way more crowded.

671
00:27:25,130 --> 00:27:27,165
They're so pretty.

672
00:27:27,165 --> 00:27:28,466
- She said we're pretty.
- I think so.

673
00:27:28,466 --> 00:27:30,835
That was about us, right?

674
00:27:30,835 --> 00:27:31,936
You always hear it

675
00:27:31,936 --> 00:27:33,404
- when someone says you're pretty, right?
- Yeah.

676
00:27:33,404 --> 00:27:36,407
- No matter how quietly they say it.
- I do have good ears, though.

677
00:27:37,542 --> 00:27:39,310
- They're ready.
- Yeah.

678
00:27:39,310 --> 00:27:40,678
Thank you.

679
00:27:40,678 --> 00:27:42,013
I threw in a few extra for you.

680
00:27:42,013 --> 00:27:43,948
- Really?
- I'm just a huge fan.

681
00:27:43,948 --> 00:27:46,618
Thank you so much.

682
00:27:46,618 --> 00:27:48,753
[A sweet little extra from a fan]
We'll enjoy them.

683
00:27:48,753 --> 00:27:51,322
- Thank you.
- Is this Season 2 of Guardian?

684
00:27:51,322 --> 00:27:53,391
It's not Season 2.

685
00:27:53,391 --> 00:27:54,959
It's a variety show.

686
00:27:54,959 --> 00:27:57,228
[It's the Guardian 10th Anniversary Trip]
I think we're a little too old for Season 2...

687
00:27:57,228 --> 00:27:59,164
Thank you.

688
00:27:59,164 --> 00:28:02,233
- Let's go now.
- Let's go.

689
00:28:02,233 --> 00:28:05,270
About another hour to go.
We're exactly halfway there.

690
00:28:05,270 --> 00:28:06,704
- Really?
- We'll be there soon.

691
00:28:06,704 --> 00:28:08,339
[Rest stop, Jumunjin]

692
00:28:08,339 --> 00:28:10,808
The place we're going is literally...

693
00:28:10,808 --> 00:28:13,378
It shows up on Google Maps
as the Guardian filming location.

694
00:28:13,378 --> 00:28:15,413
Really?

695
00:28:15,413 --> 00:28:18,082
[Guardian is a landmark now]
Yeah, it must be pretty famous.

696
00:28:18,082 --> 00:28:20,351
Also, In Na and I have never been there.

697
00:28:20,351 --> 00:28:21,686
- Right, we haven't.
- Oh, right.

698
00:28:21,686 --> 00:28:23,888
- We've only seen it on TV.
- Yeah.

699
00:28:23,888 --> 00:28:26,691
But imagine us showing up there.

700
00:28:26,691 --> 00:28:28,393
Maybe not as much these days.

701
00:28:28,393 --> 00:28:31,829
People still go there
to take pictures and look around.

702
00:28:31,829 --> 00:28:35,300
Say there are international tourists there.

703
00:28:35,300 --> 00:28:37,302
[Just imagining it is exciting]
That would blow their minds.

704
00:28:37,302 --> 00:28:40,138
If I were them, I'd lose it.

705
00:28:40,138 --> 00:28:41,873
- All four of us.
- Totally.

706
00:28:41,873 --> 00:28:43,374
The whole group together.

707
00:28:43,374 --> 00:28:44,742
[Practically a miracle]

708
00:28:44,742 --> 00:28:47,078
- Right, that never happens.
- The odds are so low...

709
00:28:47,078 --> 00:28:49,714
When people think of winter,

710
00:28:49,714 --> 00:28:52,417
Guardian is still the drama
that comes to mind, right?

711
00:28:52,417 --> 00:28:53,284
Even after ten years.

712
00:28:53,284 --> 00:28:55,186
- I don't think that's changed yet.
- Still hasn't changed, right?

713
00:28:55,186 --> 00:29:01,136
[Guardian still feels like the first snow]

714
00:29:05,163 --> 00:29:09,166
I hope it lasts as long as...

715
00:29:09,767 --> 00:29:10,968
Winter Sonata did.

716
00:29:10,968 --> 00:29:13,004
- Are we going to milk this forever?
- How long has it been?

717
00:29:13,004 --> 00:29:16,174
Almost 20 years?

718
00:29:16,174 --> 00:29:18,876
- Something like that?
- Yeah, that sounds about right.

719
00:29:21,012 --> 00:29:23,113
- What is that?
- What is that?

720
00:29:23,815 --> 00:29:25,683
[A melody that brings back memories]
Is that a ringtone?

721
00:29:25,683 --> 00:29:26,618
Why did you suddenly play that?

722
00:29:26,618 --> 00:29:29,273
[Remember the tunnel?]
- The tunnel. - The tunnel.

723
00:29:32,624 --> 00:29:33,791
[Guardian, Episode 2 ending]

724
00:29:33,791 --> 00:29:38,610
[The Goblin and Reaper go save Eun Tak]

725
00:29:40,231 --> 00:29:46,231
[Their iconic tunnel walk]

726
00:29:46,904 --> 00:29:50,585
[The green onion tunnel parody went viral]

727
00:29:52,377 --> 00:29:54,479
Stay on the sidewalk!

728
00:29:54,479 --> 00:29:56,513
Stay on the sidewalk!

729
00:29:57,782 --> 00:29:59,817
They look exactly the same as now.

730
00:29:59,817 --> 00:30:02,220
- Come on...
- Come on, we were way younger.

731
00:30:02,220 --> 00:30:05,356
- So pretty.
- You look the same.

732
00:30:05,356 --> 00:30:07,458
[Just as stunning ten years ago]
Have a blessed New Year.

733
00:30:07,458 --> 00:30:09,160
Because we look good.

734
00:30:09,160 --> 00:30:11,128
Happy New Year.

735
00:30:12,830 --> 00:30:14,365
A righteous fellow, indeed.

736
00:30:14,365 --> 00:30:16,934
People like that still exist, huh.

737
00:30:16,934 --> 00:30:17,969
Idiots. Such idiots.

738
00:30:17,969 --> 00:30:19,404
<i>A righteous fellow, indeed.</i>

739
00:30:19,404 --> 00:30:21,105
<i>People like that still exist, huh.</i>

740
00:30:21,105 --> 00:30:23,308
They're so pretty.

741
00:30:23,308 --> 00:30:25,076
Right? They're both such dorks.

742
00:30:25,076 --> 00:30:27,612
- That's what makes them cute.
- Exactly.

743
00:30:27,612 --> 00:30:30,214
If they looked like that
and were super smart too,

744
00:30:30,214 --> 00:30:31,749
- that'd be a bit much.
- Yeah.

745
00:30:31,749 --> 00:30:32,917
- They'd be hard to approach.
- You wouldn't want to hang out with them.

746
00:30:32,917 --> 00:30:34,986
[Is that... a compliment?]
What is that supposed to mean?

747
00:30:34,986 --> 00:30:38,022
- Good thing you two are dorks.
- That makes you less intimidating.

748
00:30:38,022 --> 00:30:40,391
- Not me. Just Goblin.
- Oh, please.

749
00:30:40,391 --> 00:30:42,727
- That was the dumbest thing anyone's said.
- Seriously.

750
00:30:42,727 --> 00:30:44,696
[The Goblin crew teases like breathing]
"Not me. Just Goblin."

751
00:30:44,696 --> 00:30:47,965
The ones who insist they're normal
are usually the weirdest.

752
00:30:47,965 --> 00:30:50,435
[They live to tease the guys]

753
00:30:50,435 --> 00:30:54,038
We really looked good back then.

754
00:30:54,038 --> 00:30:57,218
- I didn't know it back then.
- You never do.

755
00:30:57,218 --> 00:30:58,810
- Right.
- You just don't know it then.

756
00:30:58,810 --> 00:31:00,812
You know how that just keeps happening?

757
00:31:00,812 --> 00:31:02,246
- Yeah.
- Yeah, exactly.

758
00:31:02,246 --> 00:31:03,214
- You know what I mean?
- That's exactly it.

759
00:31:03,214 --> 00:31:05,216
- This is probably when we look our best too.
- Of course.

760
00:31:05,216 --> 00:31:06,551
So ten years from now,

761
00:31:06,551 --> 00:31:08,686
- we'll be saying the exact same thing.
- Right. We'll say the same thing.

762
00:31:08,686 --> 00:31:11,289
We'll go, "That was when we looked so good,
and we didn't even know it."

763
00:31:11,289 --> 00:31:12,724
Totally.

764
00:31:12,724 --> 00:31:14,425
But I knew it.

765
00:31:14,425 --> 00:31:15,927
- Do you know it now too?
- I mean,

766
00:31:15,927 --> 00:31:18,062
I'm looking at all three of you right now.

767
00:31:18,062 --> 00:31:20,365
When we were shooting Guardian ten years ago,

768
00:31:20,365 --> 00:31:23,485
I remember thinking,
"They're all so beautiful and cool."

769
00:31:23,485 --> 00:31:25,536
- Really?
- Yeah.

770
00:31:25,536 --> 00:31:28,239
Mid-to-late thirties is nothing.

771
00:31:28,239 --> 00:31:30,007
Right.

772
00:31:30,007 --> 00:31:32,643
Back then, I thought I was getting old too.

773
00:31:32,643 --> 00:31:33,778
But look.

774
00:31:33,778 --> 00:31:36,914
Goblin is 60, I'm 50,

775
00:31:36,914 --> 00:31:39,283
Eun Tak is 23,

776
00:31:40,318 --> 00:31:42,253
and Sunny is 28.

777
00:31:42,253 --> 00:31:44,522
[Those ages work for them]

778
00:31:44,522 --> 00:31:47,492
We like those numbers, so we're not arguing.

779
00:31:47,492 --> 00:31:50,840
[Goblin is not happy about 60]
Look at him still looking out for himself.

780
00:31:50,840 --> 00:31:53,030
- He made Goblin 60.
- He just made me ten years older than him.

781
00:31:53,030 --> 00:31:54,665
Only Goblin got older.

782
00:31:54,665 --> 00:31:56,923
[The teasing never stops]
Seriously...

783
00:31:58,536 --> 00:32:00,705
- Is that the ocean?
- Yeah, that's the ocean.

784
00:32:00,705 --> 00:32:03,674
- Is the ocean up ahead?
- Yeah, we're on the coastal road now.

785
00:32:07,145 --> 00:32:11,716
[Blue waves along the road]

786
00:32:11,716 --> 00:32:16,454
[First stop today: Jumunjin]

787
00:32:16,454 --> 00:32:18,490
[Fish Market, Guardian filming location]

788
00:32:19,524 --> 00:32:25,396
[One of Guardian's most iconic spots]

789
00:32:33,905 --> 00:32:37,442
I usually get plants for my birthday.

790
00:32:37,442 --> 00:32:40,377
When I was nine, I got cabbages.

791
00:32:42,180 --> 00:32:46,217
So what do buckwheat flowers mean?

792
00:32:46,217 --> 00:32:48,252
A lover.

793
00:32:48,252 --> 00:32:54,239
[Where Guardian's time began to move again]

794
00:33:00,198 --> 00:33:05,870
[Where that winter still lingers]

795
00:33:05,870 --> 00:33:12,810
[They've come back]

796
00:33:12,810 --> 00:33:15,563
[Feeling nostalgic]
I still remember both of your hair

797
00:33:15,563 --> 00:33:18,357
blowing in the wind back then.

798
00:33:18,357 --> 00:33:19,617
But back then, seriously,

799
00:33:19,617 --> 00:33:21,719
- the wind was insane.
- Yeah.

800
00:33:21,719 --> 00:33:23,988
It was really hard to shoot
because the wind was so strong.

801
00:33:23,988 --> 00:33:27,391
But because of that, your right hairline

802
00:33:27,391 --> 00:33:28,926
- looked amazing on camera.
- Oh, really?

803
00:33:28,926 --> 00:33:29,927
[Every day was dazzling]
Yeah.

804
00:33:29,927 --> 00:33:33,397
- It says right here, "Guardian filming location."
- Oh, you're right.

805
00:33:33,397 --> 00:33:36,100
[Finally at the Guardian filming location]

806
00:33:36,100 --> 00:33:37,602
I guess we should park here.

807
00:33:37,602 --> 00:33:39,337
There's a mural here too!

808
00:33:39,337 --> 00:33:41,506
- Oh, you're right.
- Where?

809
00:33:41,506 --> 00:33:43,941
- Oh, my!
- The mural's right here.

810
00:33:43,941 --> 00:33:46,677
Let's take a picture here.

811
00:33:48,713 --> 00:33:51,249
[Traces of Guardian all over Jumunjin]
So this is what it looks like now.

812
00:33:51,249 --> 00:33:54,085
This must feel even more special for you two.

813
00:33:54,085 --> 00:33:56,420
It really has been ten years
since we were here.

814
00:33:56,420 --> 00:33:59,924
- You're right.
- This is honestly so cool.

815
00:33:59,924 --> 00:34:02,159
It says buckwheat flowers mean "lover."

816
00:34:02,159 --> 00:34:04,095
- Lover.
- That's amazing.

817
00:34:04,095 --> 00:34:07,164
- They even have this...
- What is this? Are they asking us out?

818
00:34:07,164 --> 00:34:09,534
They're asking us out.

819
00:34:09,534 --> 00:34:11,548
[Arriving in Jumunjin]
We're here.

820
00:34:14,868 --> 00:34:16,274
So this is what you meant.

821
00:34:16,274 --> 00:34:19,010
Oh, the weather is so nice right now.

822
00:34:19,010 --> 00:34:21,145
It's perfectly cool. It's not hot.

823
00:34:21,145 --> 00:34:23,147
- Not cold either.
- The breeze is perfect.

824
00:34:23,147 --> 00:34:24,847
It is.

825
00:34:25,650 --> 00:34:27,851
That breeze feels so good.

826
00:34:31,923 --> 00:34:34,292
[The baby bolts for the ocean]

827
00:34:34,292 --> 00:34:36,560
It's the ocean!

828
00:34:39,030 --> 00:34:42,066
- Hello.
- Hello.

829
00:34:42,066 --> 00:34:43,434
Hello.

830
00:34:43,434 --> 00:34:45,736
[Still says hello on the way]

831
00:34:45,736 --> 00:34:47,071
Where did she go?

832
00:34:47,071 --> 00:34:48,973
She's going off by herself.

833
00:34:48,973 --> 00:34:51,275
We have to go together.

834
00:34:51,876 --> 00:34:53,210
"We have to go together."

835
00:34:53,210 --> 00:34:55,146
We have to go together.

836
00:34:55,146 --> 00:34:57,481
Eun Tak, come here.

837
00:34:57,481 --> 00:35:00,284
[After rounding up the runaway baby]

838
00:35:00,284 --> 00:35:01,419
What?

839
00:35:01,419 --> 00:35:03,045
Right here. You two should take some pictures.

840
00:35:03,045 --> 00:35:06,490
- That's him. That's really him.
- That's him?

841
00:35:06,490 --> 00:35:08,893
[In Na proudly shows off the Goblin couple]
I mean, that's really the guy.

842
00:35:08,893 --> 00:35:10,761
He's the real person.

843
00:35:10,761 --> 00:35:12,463
- Really?
- Yes.

844
00:35:12,463 --> 00:35:14,732
[The real ones, standing by the mural]

845
00:35:14,732 --> 00:35:16,267
I knew they looked familiar.

846
00:35:16,267 --> 00:35:17,335
Yes, exactly.

847
00:35:17,335 --> 00:35:19,503
- I've seen them on TV so many times!
- That's right. That's Gong Yoo.

848
00:35:19,503 --> 00:35:23,407
He's Goblin! He's the lead.

849
00:35:23,407 --> 00:35:25,695
Is this supposed to be buckwheat flowers?

850
00:35:25,695 --> 00:35:28,386
[Stand-in buckwheat flowers]

851
00:35:29,480 --> 00:35:32,350
- They're the leads?
- Yes, they're the leads.

852
00:35:32,350 --> 00:35:33,818
And me too.

853
00:35:33,818 --> 00:35:36,520
- Oh, my goodness.
- All four of us are the leads.

854
00:35:36,520 --> 00:35:37,688
[Guardian comes to life ten years later]

855
00:35:37,688 --> 00:35:40,458
Do I look too old now?

856
00:35:40,458 --> 00:35:42,793
- Too old?
- Yeah.

857
00:35:42,793 --> 00:35:44,128
Dad, look at me.

858
00:35:44,128 --> 00:35:45,829
Your dad?

859
00:35:46,758 --> 00:35:50,088
That drawing doesn't even have a face.
What are you talking about?

860
00:35:51,602 --> 00:35:52,970
[Eun Tak and Goblin meet again]

861
00:35:52,970 --> 00:35:55,306
Okay, that's good.

862
00:35:55,306 --> 00:35:56,607
- Yeah.
- Let's go to the real spot.

863
00:35:56,607 --> 00:35:58,843
- Yeah, let's go.
- I brought the scarf.

864
00:35:58,843 --> 00:36:00,444
The one the doll was wearing.

865
00:36:00,444 --> 00:36:03,314
- Let's do it at the Jumunjin spot.
- Yeah, do it there.

866
00:36:03,314 --> 00:36:05,849
- I'll hold on to it. Do it when we get there.
- Let's go.

867
00:36:08,719 --> 00:36:11,422
[Into an iconic Guardian scene
with Eun Tak's scarf]

868
00:36:11,422 --> 00:36:12,568
Doesn't the ocean smell nice?

869
00:36:12,568 --> 00:36:14,759
- Because it's been so long?
- It's nice.

870
00:36:14,759 --> 00:36:17,561
- The ocean is just so...
- Hey, the drone.

871
00:36:17,561 --> 00:36:19,764
- Where? Where is it?
- Say hi to the drone.

872
00:36:19,764 --> 00:36:22,065
The drone!

873
00:36:22,700 --> 00:36:24,869
- Hey!
- We really do whatever we're told.

874
00:36:24,869 --> 00:36:26,871
- Did we shoot here or over there?
- I don't know either.

875
00:36:26,871 --> 00:36:28,372
- I can't remember.
- I think it's over there.

876
00:36:28,372 --> 00:36:30,675
Eun Tak, this wasn't
this short back then, was it?

877
00:36:30,675 --> 00:36:32,076
Wasn't it longer?

878
00:36:32,076 --> 00:36:34,845
- Was it always this short?
- That's why I'm confused.

879
00:36:34,845 --> 00:36:37,214
[Two similar breakwaters side by side]
I can't tell if it was here or there.

880
00:36:37,214 --> 00:36:40,051
- But the waves were crashing like this.
- They really were.

881
00:36:40,051 --> 00:36:42,486
- What month was that?
- There's a sign over there.

882
00:36:42,486 --> 00:36:44,088
What month was it again?

883
00:36:44,088 --> 00:36:45,423
Was it around October?

884
00:36:45,423 --> 00:36:47,193
I don't think it was October.

885
00:36:47,193 --> 00:36:48,959
At first, what was it...

886
00:36:48,959 --> 00:36:51,762
- He was wearing ivory!
- Right! And black pants.

887
00:36:51,762 --> 00:36:53,700
- That was when...
- At the very beginning.

888
00:36:53,700 --> 00:36:55,566
- On Eun Tak's birthday!
- That was the beginning.

889
00:36:55,566 --> 00:36:56,434
That was early on.

890
00:36:56,434 --> 00:36:57,768
I was standing there
with the buckwheat flowers.

891
00:36:57,768 --> 00:37:00,237
- And you asked what they were and wanted them?
- Yeah.

892
00:37:00,237 --> 00:37:01,772
You're so excited right now.

893
00:37:01,772 --> 00:37:03,541
- He...
- Hey, someone's there!

894
00:37:03,541 --> 00:37:05,576
- He...
- Hey, someone's there!

895
00:37:05,576 --> 00:37:07,311
They're taking pictures over there right now.

896
00:37:07,311 --> 00:37:09,814
Gosh. Go ask if they want you
to take their picture!

897
00:37:09,814 --> 00:37:12,883
- That would make their whole day.
- Go take their picture for them!

898
00:37:12,883 --> 00:37:16,520
[Still remembering Guardian
after all these years]

899
00:37:19,290 --> 00:37:21,308
They're even passing the scarf back and forth.

900
00:37:21,308 --> 00:37:23,928
- Oh, my gosh, really?
- That's amazing.

901
00:37:23,928 --> 00:37:25,930
[They even brought the red scarf]
Hey, did people do stuff like this back then?

902
00:37:25,930 --> 00:37:27,398
Probably not, right?

903
00:37:27,398 --> 00:37:28,632
I think they did.

904
00:37:28,632 --> 00:37:29,600
- They did?
- Yeah.

905
00:37:29,600 --> 00:37:30,668
I'm such a huge fan!

906
00:37:30,668 --> 00:37:31,581
- Thank you.
- Hi.

907
00:37:31,581 --> 00:37:32,670
Hello.

908
00:37:32,670 --> 00:37:34,038
[Thrilled]

909
00:37:34,038 --> 00:37:35,940
Oh, this feels so good.

910
00:37:35,940 --> 00:37:38,476
- The weather is perfect.
- Seriously.

911
00:37:38,476 --> 00:37:40,911
Take off your sunglasses.

912
00:37:42,446 --> 00:37:43,848
Oh, man.

913
00:37:43,848 --> 00:37:45,750
Once you take them off...

914
00:37:45,750 --> 00:37:47,485
- So this is what daylight looks like.
- Really?

915
00:37:47,485 --> 00:37:48,826
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

916
00:37:49,553 --> 00:37:52,323
[Because the day is beautiful]

917
00:37:52,323 --> 00:37:53,524
Is this the right spot?

918
00:37:53,524 --> 00:37:54,792
[Everything feels perfect]

919
00:37:54,792 --> 00:37:56,694
- I don't know. They said it is.
- Try to remember, you two!

920
00:37:56,694 --> 00:37:57,728
[The Peach Couple's first time in Jumunjin]

921
00:37:57,728 --> 00:37:59,863
It's our first time here.

922
00:38:00,498 --> 00:38:02,533
- Hello.
- Hello.

923
00:38:02,533 --> 00:38:03,701
- Hi.
- Hello.

924
00:38:03,701 --> 00:38:05,069
- Hello.
- Hello.

925
00:38:05,069 --> 00:38:06,370
- Hello.
- Hello.

926
00:38:06,370 --> 00:38:08,139
They really are international fans.

927
00:38:08,139 --> 00:38:09,240
- They're international fans?
- They are international fans.

928
00:38:09,240 --> 00:38:13,643
[The Goblin appears at a Guardian landmark]
Was it always worn down like this?

929
00:38:15,980 --> 00:38:17,848
[Wave crashes]

930
00:38:17,848 --> 00:38:20,750
Yeah, it was like this back then.

931
00:38:24,021 --> 00:38:26,590
That's the exact ocean color from Guardian.

932
00:38:26,590 --> 00:38:29,693
[The waves roll in to welcome them]
It was just like this.

933
00:38:29,693 --> 00:38:32,696
Right. I think we got
a little wet filming here too.

934
00:38:32,696 --> 00:38:35,878
This is definitely the place! That's the rock

935
00:38:35,878 --> 00:38:38,269
where Eun Tak left her bag.

936
00:38:38,269 --> 00:38:39,470
What?

937
00:38:39,470 --> 00:38:40,971
You remember that?

938
00:38:40,971 --> 00:38:42,139
Eun Tak's bag was...

939
00:38:42,139 --> 00:38:43,574
- Stop lying.
- Stop making stuff up.

940
00:38:43,574 --> 00:38:45,442
Seriously, do you want to check it later?

941
00:38:45,442 --> 00:38:47,912
- Come on, stop lying.
- Show the clip!

942
00:38:47,912 --> 00:38:51,549
[She was right. It was the far end]
Is this rain ever going to stop?

943
00:38:51,549 --> 00:38:53,551
I only have two umbrellas,

944
00:38:53,551 --> 00:38:55,886
so why does it keep raining like this?

945
00:38:55,886 --> 00:38:58,389
[Eun Tak vented from that very rock]

946
00:38:58,389 --> 00:39:00,825
- Oh, man, it's cold.
- I think I sat around here and cried.

947
00:39:00,825 --> 00:39:02,326
Wait, it was here, not there?

948
00:39:02,326 --> 00:39:03,394
This right here?

949
00:39:03,394 --> 00:39:06,372
- Wasn't it at the very end?
- I think we moved around and cheated the shot.

950
00:39:06,372 --> 00:39:08,899
So we were doing this...

951
00:39:08,899 --> 00:39:10,701
- The waves kept crashing in.
- Right.

952
00:39:10,701 --> 00:39:11,902
It's cold.

953
00:39:11,902 --> 00:39:14,137
This is rough.

954
00:39:15,172 --> 00:39:17,074
It's cold.

955
00:39:17,074 --> 00:39:19,917
[The Grim Reaper can't take the cold]

956
00:39:23,113 --> 00:39:24,915
That's cute.

957
00:39:25,549 --> 00:39:28,618
This feels so strange.

958
00:39:30,387 --> 00:39:32,255
Let's take pictures too!

959
00:39:32,857 --> 00:39:35,259
My hair...

960
00:39:35,259 --> 00:39:36,894
The wind here is still... Hey, my hair...

961
00:39:36,894 --> 00:39:40,158
[The Goblin couple makes new memories]

962
00:39:40,158 --> 00:39:42,533
Hey, Eun Tak, get one with him.

963
00:39:42,533 --> 00:39:44,568
Yeah, be careful.

964
00:39:46,837 --> 00:39:48,873
- We shouldn't go any farther.
- Are you really scared?

965
00:39:48,873 --> 00:39:50,941
- Are you okay?
- Yeah... I'm scared.

966
00:39:50,941 --> 00:39:52,343
What is this? Where did you get it?

967
00:39:52,343 --> 00:39:55,546
This was in the car too.

968
00:39:55,546 --> 00:39:58,249
[In Na came ready for full Guardian mode]

969
00:39:58,249 --> 00:40:01,585
- I'm so excited. I want to take pictures.
- Hey, let's look around.

970
00:40:02,186 --> 00:40:04,667
- My hair is probably going to look crazy.
- No, you look pretty right now.

971
00:40:04,667 --> 00:40:06,490
- Your hair looks pretty. It looks natural.
- Messy hair actually works for the scene.

972
00:40:06,490 --> 00:40:07,658
- Your hair was messy back then.
- But...

973
00:40:07,658 --> 00:40:09,560
- The pictures are coming out so good.
- My hair was short back then.

974
00:40:09,560 --> 00:40:11,295
Was I holding this?

975
00:40:11,295 --> 00:40:13,731
- Yeah, and then I asked for it.
- I was holding it, then you asked for it.

976
00:40:13,731 --> 00:40:15,751
- Did I give it to you?
- Of course you did.

977
00:40:15,751 --> 00:40:18,274
She was like, "It's my birthday today."

978
00:40:18,274 --> 00:40:21,269
She was like, "It's my birthday today."

979
00:40:21,939 --> 00:40:23,537
Ah, this feels so weird.

980
00:40:23,537 --> 00:40:25,724
- How are you exactly the same?
- This feels weird.

981
00:40:25,724 --> 00:40:29,480
- You haven't changed a bit, Go Eun.
- It's my birthday today.

982
00:40:29,480 --> 00:40:31,453
[Still-vivid memories from a past life]
It's my birthday today.

983
00:40:31,453 --> 00:40:35,003
Give it to me. It doesn't suit you, mister.

984
00:40:35,003 --> 00:40:38,074
- It doesn't suit you, mister.
- Whoa, this feels so weird!

985
00:40:38,074 --> 00:40:41,268
Man, this feels weird. It really feels weird.

986
00:40:41,268 --> 00:40:43,220
How does it feel weird?
Are you getting emotional?

987
00:40:43,220 --> 00:40:45,516
No, I'm not getting emotional...

988
00:40:45,516 --> 00:40:47,996
It just feels kind of creepy.

989
00:40:49,259 --> 00:40:51,843
[Present-day Ji Eun Tak looks exactly the same]
You look exactly the same as you did back then.

990
00:40:51,843 --> 00:40:55,019
- With her suddenly saying that...
- You look exactly the same too.

991
00:40:55,019 --> 00:40:57,167
[I'll take the picture]
- You should take a picture. - Hurry, take it!

992
00:40:57,167 --> 00:40:59,294
Ah, Yoo In Na's terrible at taking pictures.

993
00:40:59,294 --> 00:41:02,345
[Lots of enthusiasm, but no talent]
- Seriously... - What are you doing?

994
00:41:02,345 --> 00:41:06,205
[Eun Tak and the Goblin
face each other once again]

995
00:41:06,205 --> 00:41:08,248
[They just can't stop laughing]

996
00:41:08,248 --> 00:41:10,727
- Will you get it together?
- I'm telling you, it feels weird.

997
00:41:10,727 --> 00:41:13,306
- Let's hurry, take the picture, and go!
- Stand still for a second!

998
00:41:13,306 --> 00:41:16,273
- Move a little closer. Just a little.
- Ugh, this is so cheesy.

999
00:41:16,273 --> 00:41:18,313
Man, I don't even know
how we did this back then.

1000
00:41:18,313 --> 00:41:21,129
- Take your glasses off!
- I'll step back.

1001
00:41:22,159 --> 00:41:24,902
- I'm so happy to watch this.
- Really?

1002
00:41:28,342 --> 00:41:30,879
- Look at each other for a second.
- Hey! Can't you focus?

1003
00:41:30,879 --> 00:41:32,521
- I can't focus...
- Look at each other. Come on.

1004
00:41:32,521 --> 00:41:35,099
Look at me. Look at me!

1005
00:41:47,535 --> 00:41:53,505
[Kim Shin and Eun Tak,
whose every moment was destiny]

1006
00:41:58,636 --> 00:42:01,169
[Live another ten years]
Don't move. Let them take the picture.

1007
00:42:01,169 --> 00:42:05,672
[And one day, on a perfectly ordinary day]
You have to stay still so they can take it.

1008
00:42:05,672 --> 00:42:08,052
[They've found each other once again]

1009
00:42:08,052 --> 00:42:09,480
Did you get it?

1010
00:42:09,480 --> 00:42:11,742
- I'm exactly the same as I was back then.
- How?

1011
00:42:11,742 --> 00:42:15,595
My hair kept doing this back then too.
I remember I kept turning this way and that.

1012
00:42:16,442 --> 00:42:18,508
[Completely immersed]

1013
00:42:18,508 --> 00:42:20,742
Okay, okay. We got all the pictures.

1014
00:42:20,742 --> 00:42:24,389
- Okay, we're done now.
- This is so embarrassing.

1015
00:42:24,389 --> 00:42:27,683
- Come on, it's a great memory.
- Hang on.

1016
00:42:29,823 --> 00:42:33,483
[Putting her scarf on him
while another fixes her outfit]

1017
00:42:33,483 --> 00:42:35,227
- Hey, you two, go over there.
- Yeah, go ahead.

1018
00:42:35,227 --> 00:42:37,618
[The Peach Couple
gets into position on their own]

1019
00:42:37,618 --> 00:42:39,016
Hey, this is kind of like...

1020
00:42:39,016 --> 00:42:40,580
I should be the one giving this
to you, Dong Wook!

1021
00:42:40,580 --> 00:42:42,093
- You're supposed to...
- But I was the one who did that.

1022
00:42:42,093 --> 00:42:43,098
- That's so cute.
- Exactly.

1023
00:42:43,098 --> 00:42:46,471
[Playing Eun Tak, Playing the Goblin]
So now I should give it to you.

1024
00:42:46,471 --> 00:42:50,620
- Was that how it went originally?
- Yeah, that's how it goes.

1025
00:42:50,620 --> 00:42:52,541
You're supposed to say, "Give me the flowers."

1026
00:42:52,541 --> 00:42:53,842
Give me the flowers.

1027
00:42:53,842 --> 00:42:55,114
You have to say, "It's my birthday," too.

1028
00:42:55,114 --> 00:42:56,961
- It's my birthday.
- You're even doing the lines?

1029
00:42:56,961 --> 00:42:59,881
Then ask me what this flower is called.

1030
00:42:59,881 --> 00:43:03,141
- What's the meaning of this flower?
- "Lovers!"

1031
00:43:04,753 --> 00:43:07,479
Now we have no choice but to be lovers!

1032
00:43:07,479 --> 00:43:10,926
[Sunny-Goblin lifts Grim Reaper Eun Tak]
She just loudly goes, "Lovers!"

1033
00:43:10,926 --> 00:43:12,366
- "Lovers!"
- "Lovers!"

1034
00:43:12,366 --> 00:43:13,477
"Lovers!"

1035
00:43:13,477 --> 00:43:16,045
- Hey, let's all take a picture together.
- Good, good.

1036
00:43:16,045 --> 00:43:18,318
- I'll hold it.
- Put this scarf on.

1037
00:43:18,318 --> 00:43:19,584
No, I'm not cold.

1038
00:43:19,584 --> 00:43:21,318
[A commemorative photo
at a place full of memories]

1039
00:43:23,326 --> 00:43:25,056
- Wave, wave!
- Let's have Go Eun hold this.

1040
00:43:25,056 --> 00:43:28,050
Move her in a little!

1041
00:43:28,050 --> 00:43:31,759
- You're the one moving into the middle.
- No...

1042
00:43:31,759 --> 00:43:34,559
Go Eun, put this on and hold this.

1043
00:43:35,639 --> 00:43:38,488
- Seriously...
- What a dummy.

1044
00:43:38,488 --> 00:43:40,507
- That sign over there.
- Which one?

1045
00:43:40,507 --> 00:43:42,747
- Oh, "Goblin!"
- Yeah.

1046
00:43:50,866 --> 00:43:54,311
[The scattered moments in time
come together again]

1047
00:43:56,085 --> 00:43:59,216
[The memories that had stopped
begin to flow again]

1048
00:44:04,204 --> 00:44:06,164
It felt so strange hearing you say those lines.

1049
00:44:06,164 --> 00:44:09,276
[A brilliant story begins again]
- Really? - Yeah, it felt really weird.

1050
00:44:09,276 --> 00:44:11,463
My whole body feels heavy.

1051
00:44:19,518 --> 00:44:25,533
[The Goblin family heads to
a nearby restaurant]

1052
00:44:25,533 --> 00:44:28,033
Go Eun Tak! It's only 20 minutes
to the place after we eat.

1053
00:44:28,033 --> 00:44:29,406
Do you want to drive?

1054
00:44:29,406 --> 00:44:31,078
- No, no. I'll do it, I'll drive!
- Yeah.

1055
00:44:31,078 --> 00:44:33,125
- When we eat there...
- Yeah.

1056
00:44:33,125 --> 00:44:35,325
Have some soju with Eun Tak.

1057
00:44:35,325 --> 00:44:38,757
[Grins]
Have some soju. How could you not...

1058
00:44:38,757 --> 00:44:41,277
- We have to have a shot of soju...
- Yeah, that's why I'll drive.

1059
00:44:41,277 --> 00:44:42,736
Since I'm not drinking.

1060
00:44:42,736 --> 00:44:46,017
Then you three have a drink.
I'll be the driver.

1061
00:44:46,017 --> 00:44:48,791
No, no, In Na. Then it's better to take a taxi.

1062
00:44:50,632 --> 00:44:51,541
If In Na drives...

1063
00:44:51,541 --> 00:44:53,693
[Sweetly rejected]
- Completely ignored. - If In Na is driving...

1064
00:44:53,693 --> 00:44:57,411
Wow, being rejected
that sweetly is pretty unique.

1065
00:44:57,411 --> 00:44:58,545
In Na, it's okay.

1066
00:44:58,545 --> 00:45:00,837
[Heading to the restaurant
with sweet consideration]

1067
00:45:00,837 --> 00:45:04,030
Wow, I really felt weird earlier.

1068
00:45:04,030 --> 00:45:05,670
- Really? What felt so strange?
- I don't know.

1069
00:45:05,670 --> 00:45:08,566
I kept thinking about why it felt so strange.

1070
00:45:08,566 --> 00:45:13,479
But she's definitely the same Eun Tak...

1071
00:45:13,479 --> 00:45:15,527
But she feels so much more grown-up now.

1072
00:45:15,527 --> 00:45:18,410
[Like meeting a more grown-up Eun Tak]
Ah! That's true.

1073
00:45:18,410 --> 00:45:22,424
But saying the exact same lines
in the same tone felt kind of strange.

1074
00:45:22,424 --> 00:45:26,266
For us, who watched Eun Tak grow up,
it makes sense.

1075
00:45:26,266 --> 00:45:28,809
- I guess that's probably it.
- Right.

1076
00:45:28,809 --> 00:45:31,502
You watched everything from the side...

1077
00:45:34,395 --> 00:45:38,539
Wow! The ocean is amazing! This feels so nice.

1078
00:45:38,539 --> 00:45:40,774
- It's been such a long time since I saw this.
- I know.

1079
00:45:40,774 --> 00:45:42,807
- The weather is really helping us.
- Exactly.

1080
00:45:42,807 --> 00:45:44,248
We picked the perfect day.

1081
00:45:44,248 --> 00:45:45,321
[Slowly looking back on the past 10 years]

1082
00:45:45,321 --> 00:45:48,585
Exactly, we planned this so long ago.
How can the weather be this perfect?

1083
00:45:48,585 --> 00:45:51,835
- Should we go in? Or park here?
- Oh, I guess this is where we park.

1084
00:45:51,835 --> 00:45:54,761
- Suddenly, I'm hungry.
- Wow, this place must be really famous.

1085
00:45:54,761 --> 00:45:56,481
[Arriving at a restaurant near Jumunjin]
I'm suddenly so excited.

1086
00:45:56,481 --> 00:45:59,394
- Oh, I'm hungry.
- Yeah, me too.

1087
00:45:59,394 --> 00:46:01,361
It looks like a painting. It really does!

1088
00:46:01,361 --> 00:46:03,187
Wow, the weather feels unreal.

1089
00:46:03,187 --> 00:46:06,168
[The blue scenery of Jumunjin
turns into a picture-like view]

1090
00:46:06,168 --> 00:46:10,166
Wow! Should we check the menu?

1091
00:46:10,166 --> 00:46:12,634
Can't we just order one and share it?

1092
00:46:12,634 --> 00:46:14,743
Ah, this place's signature dish is mulhoe.

1093
00:46:14,743 --> 00:46:17,355
- Assorted mulhoe.
- Great! I wanted to eat mulhoe.

1094
00:46:17,355 --> 00:46:20,124
- Want to have abalone porridge or something?
- Yeah! Sounds good.

1095
00:46:20,124 --> 00:46:22,326
What raw fish is in season here?

1096
00:46:22,326 --> 00:46:24,790
We have black porgy, flounder, and maraemi.

1097
00:46:24,790 --> 00:46:26,021
- Maraemi?
- It's a young yellowtail.

1098
00:46:26,021 --> 00:46:29,869
- A baby yellowtail is called maraemi.
- Oh, in the local term...

1099
00:46:29,869 --> 00:46:30,941
Let's have that.

1100
00:46:30,941 --> 00:46:32,502
- Should we order something small?
- Yeah.

1101
00:46:32,502 --> 00:46:33,963
Let's try it! When will we get the chance?

1102
00:46:33,963 --> 00:46:36,779
One small order of wild raw fish,

1103
00:46:36,779 --> 00:46:40,033
one assorted mulhoe,
and abalone porridge, please.

1104
00:46:40,033 --> 00:46:41,368
- Okay, we'll prepare it for you.
- Yeah.

1105
00:46:41,368 --> 00:46:43,638
- Thank you. Aren't you drinking anything?
- Yeah.

1106
00:46:43,638 --> 00:46:46,797
[Deep contemplation]

1107
00:46:46,797 --> 00:46:49,227
- What should we do?
- Drink! I'll drive.

1108
00:46:49,227 --> 00:46:52,851
I told you I'd drive, seriously!
The three of you drink.

1109
00:46:52,851 --> 00:46:55,551
In Na, if that's the case,
it's better to take a taxi...

1110
00:46:56,331 --> 00:46:57,836
That's so funny.

1111
00:46:57,836 --> 00:47:00,537
What should we do? Raw fish calls for a drink.

1112
00:47:00,537 --> 00:47:02,067
- Exactly.
- Just order one.

1113
00:47:02,067 --> 00:47:04,516
- That just wouldn't feel right, would it?
- One bottle of soju too, please.

1114
00:47:04,516 --> 00:47:08,396
Hey, the four of us have eaten
together before, right?

1115
00:47:08,396 --> 00:47:09,869
Of course we have! Why wouldn't we?

1116
00:47:09,869 --> 00:47:13,135
- Oh, we've spent a lot of time together.
- When did we start?

1117
00:47:13,135 --> 00:47:15,480
- I think that was probably September...
- Late July? November?

1118
00:47:15,480 --> 00:47:17,455
- Wasn't it then?
- September? Oh, really?

1119
00:47:17,455 --> 00:47:19,458
[The first filming scene of the Goblin couple?]
The very first thing we filmed was...

1120
00:47:19,458 --> 00:47:21,769
- we weren't even close at first...
- That one.

1121
00:47:21,769 --> 00:47:24,008
- The buckwheat field, yeah.
- And they told us to kiss.

1122
00:47:24,008 --> 00:47:26,838
- At the buckwheat field?
- Yeah, the director apologized.

1123
00:47:26,838 --> 00:47:29,118
- In the buckwheat field...
- It was our first shoot, and we just...

1124
00:47:29,118 --> 00:47:31,253
[The kiss was filmed before the flowers faded]
- Those buckwheat flowers... - Right!

1125
00:47:31,253 --> 00:47:34,247
- Because they were going to fade.
- That's right.

1126
00:47:34,247 --> 00:47:36,006
So it happened that way because of the timing.

1127
00:47:36,006 --> 00:47:37,382
- That was the first scene we filmed.
- They said we had to film that first.

1128
00:47:37,382 --> 00:47:38,504
Right, the first shoot.

1129
00:47:38,504 --> 00:47:42,700
Back then, the two of us
were kind of stiff and awkward.

1130
00:47:42,700 --> 00:47:46,286
Mister, there's always somewhere
wonderful behind your door.

1131
00:47:46,286 --> 00:47:48,932
Do you have any final words?

1132
00:47:50,479 --> 00:47:55,550
Every moment I spent with you was dazzling.

1133
00:47:59,010 --> 00:48:01,223
Because the weather was good,

1134
00:48:03,250 --> 00:48:05,883
because the weather was bad,

1135
00:48:07,951 --> 00:48:10,504
because the weather was just right...

1136
00:48:13,744 --> 00:48:16,373
every day was beautiful.

1137
00:48:16,373 --> 00:48:18,312
[And the first kiss scene of their first shoot]

1138
00:48:18,312 --> 00:48:20,062
A kiss.

1139
00:48:23,063 --> 00:48:29,063
[Their first kiss when they were
still awkward with each other]

1140
00:48:35,992 --> 00:48:37,904
- Do you remember our first shoot?
- Yeah!

1141
00:48:37,904 --> 00:48:39,395
What? I don't remember.

1142
00:48:39,395 --> 00:48:40,801
- Really?
- Yeah.

1143
00:48:40,801 --> 00:48:43,907
Then I'll give you some choices.

1144
00:48:43,907 --> 00:48:46,120
Ah, just tell me!

1145
00:48:47,049 --> 00:48:48,896
- Give it to me. I'll guess.
- Give us the choices.

1146
00:48:48,896 --> 00:48:51,194
- Let's all guess.
- I knew it from when you said "Really?"

1147
00:48:51,194 --> 00:48:54,589
[MC Sunny Quiz Time, let's all guess]
Number 1, on the overpass.

1148
00:48:54,589 --> 00:48:56,743
[Grim Reaper & Sunny's first filming location]
- Yeah, the overpass. - The overpass.

1149
00:48:56,743 --> 00:49:00,298
The overpass is where we first
meet in the drama.

1150
00:49:00,298 --> 00:49:01,424
How much is this?

1151
00:49:01,424 --> 00:49:02,932
[In front of the stall on the overpass]

1152
00:49:03,978 --> 00:49:08,402
[The first meeting of Grim Reaper and Sunny]

1153
00:49:11,309 --> 00:49:12,867
I picked it up first.

1154
00:49:12,867 --> 00:49:16,064
Oh, just because of that... are you crying?

1155
00:49:16,064 --> 00:49:19,295
[The first encounter on the overpass
that made Grim Reaper cry]

1156
00:49:19,295 --> 00:49:22,145
Number 2, the chicken restaurant.

1157
00:49:22,145 --> 00:49:24,699
He's disappearing again.

1158
00:49:24,699 --> 00:49:26,859
I'm sorry, it wasn't intentional.

1159
00:49:26,859 --> 00:49:28,278
[Sunny's workplace,
where their romance slowly grows]

1160
00:49:28,278 --> 00:49:32,791
Do I really have to be the one
to reach out to him first, like I'm desperate?

1161
00:49:33,464 --> 00:49:35,278
Now?

1162
00:49:35,278 --> 00:49:39,331
<i>- Are you busy?</i>
- Yes, I'm going crazy.

1163
00:49:41,030 --> 00:49:42,723
<i>What are you doing right now?</i>

1164
00:49:42,723 --> 00:49:46,550
I'm taking off the pattern lock
because I'm afraid it'll make noise again.

1165
00:49:48,858 --> 00:49:50,838
- Yeah.
- Number 3,

1166
00:49:50,838 --> 00:49:52,682
[3. Cafe]
the cafe.

1167
00:49:52,682 --> 00:49:54,258
Cafe?

1168
00:49:54,258 --> 00:49:55,946
- Overpass!
- Overpass?

1169
00:49:55,946 --> 00:49:58,571
- I also say overpass.
- Overpass, overpass? What about you?

1170
00:49:58,571 --> 00:50:00,210
- I also say overpass.
- Overpass?

1171
00:50:00,210 --> 00:50:03,597
You're wrong! I said you're wrong!

1172
00:50:03,597 --> 00:50:05,556
- Is it the cafe?
- It's the cafe.

1173
00:50:05,556 --> 00:50:07,492
- It's the cafe?
- Yeah, it's the cafe.

1174
00:50:07,492 --> 00:50:10,363
- What are you? You filmed it yourself.
- Which cafe scene?

1175
00:50:10,363 --> 00:50:14,149
At the cafe... I'll give you choices.

1176
00:50:14,149 --> 00:50:15,790
[MC Sunny's endless choice quiz]

1177
00:50:15,790 --> 00:50:17,492
What is it? What...

1178
00:50:17,492 --> 00:50:19,456
This is so fun though. I'm enjoying this!

1179
00:50:19,456 --> 00:50:20,749
- I'll give you the choices.
- Yeah.

1180
00:50:20,749 --> 00:50:24,223
[Sunny's quiz continues]
- One, with Sung Jae... - Yeah.

1181
00:50:24,223 --> 00:50:27,578
[1. Grim Reaper & Yoo Deok Hwa 2-on-2 meeting]
- That scene with my friend... - Oh, yeah.

1182
00:50:27,578 --> 00:50:31,464
- Number 2 is "Sunny!"
- Yeah, "Sunny."

1183
00:50:31,464 --> 00:50:34,677
- What do you like, Mr. Woo Bin?
- You, Sunny.

1184
00:50:36,992 --> 00:50:38,852
I'm going crazy...

1185
00:50:38,852 --> 00:50:42,025
Number 3 is...
"Why aren't you answering my calls?"

1186
00:50:42,025 --> 00:50:43,518
Isn't that the "Sunny" one?

1187
00:50:43,518 --> 00:50:47,051
No... but what was the scene,
what was it again?

1188
00:50:47,051 --> 00:50:50,706
- Just guess the number. One, two, or three.
- Wait...

1189
00:50:50,706 --> 00:50:53,547
- What? What was number 3?
- It's number 3! It's number 3.

1190
00:50:54,247 --> 00:50:55,776
[The answer blurted out by accident]
- Right, it's number 3. - It's number 3.

1191
00:50:55,776 --> 00:50:57,037
- What was number 3?
- I don't know.

1192
00:50:57,037 --> 00:51:01,457
So here's the thing. In that scene,
his hair is noticeably shorter.

1193
00:51:01,457 --> 00:51:05,020
Be honest. You forgot my name, didn't you?

1194
00:51:05,020 --> 00:51:06,639
[Especially short hair]

1195
00:51:06,639 --> 00:51:09,840
- Sun Hee.
- Not Sun Hee, it's Sunny!

1196
00:51:14,792 --> 00:51:18,191
You're really... a funny man.

1197
00:51:20,564 --> 00:51:23,644
He had a really bad cold, like a severe one.

1198
00:51:23,644 --> 00:51:24,918
Oh come on. You're so weak!

1199
00:51:24,918 --> 00:51:29,531
When we got to the first scene,
he came in coughing and sniffling.

1200
00:51:29,531 --> 00:51:31,231
- I was pretending to be pitiful.
- You looked pitiful.

1201
00:51:31,231 --> 00:51:34,718
- So I just stayed quiet.
- Wait, wait.

1202
00:51:34,718 --> 00:51:36,493
But I feel like this isn't going to
be a good story.

1203
00:51:36,493 --> 00:51:39,019
- It's not a good story!
- Should we stop?

1204
00:51:39,019 --> 00:51:41,536
[I got a feeling]
- Oh, this is so funny! - Should we stop?

1205
00:51:41,536 --> 00:51:43,247
No, for a moment, I suddenly felt it!

1206
00:51:43,247 --> 00:51:45,006
- I don't think this is going to be good.
- This is a bit...

1207
00:51:45,006 --> 00:51:47,919
Wait, In Na, this isn't your first time
telling this story, right?

1208
00:51:47,919 --> 00:51:50,499
- No, it's her first time telling it.
- I'm telling it for the very first time.

1209
00:51:50,499 --> 00:51:52,972
- That was the character you showed me.
- Yeah.

1210
00:51:52,972 --> 00:51:56,851
Because when you first see
Dong-Reaper, he's kind of...

1211
00:51:56,851 --> 00:51:58,452
- You were kind of...
- I was just kind of indifferent, I guess.

1212
00:51:58,452 --> 00:52:01,973
- Well, even just saying hello...
- But he was actually sick.

1213
00:52:01,973 --> 00:52:04,871
- You did it like that.
- Hey, I wasn't that bad!

1214
00:52:04,871 --> 00:52:08,997
- Why are you trying to ruin me?
- Let's ruin him, everyone.

1215
00:52:09,998 --> 00:52:11,257
That's how you were back then.

1216
00:52:11,257 --> 00:52:14,394
But after seeing you a few times,
you started taking care of people.

1217
00:52:14,394 --> 00:52:16,129
[His sweet side comes out when he gets close]
- "Want some water?" - Then...

1218
00:52:16,129 --> 00:52:18,003
But then, a little while after that,

1219
00:52:18,003 --> 00:52:20,136
when I asked, "Did you catch a cold?"

1220
00:52:20,136 --> 00:52:22,176
[Dong Wook's role with a cold]
"Ugh, this cold..."

1221
00:52:22,176 --> 00:52:24,838
[Nervous fingertips]
"Ah, it suddenly got much worse last night."

1222
00:52:24,838 --> 00:52:29,845
"My fever went up to 39°C. I almost died."
That's what he said.

1223
00:52:29,845 --> 00:52:31,287
What do you even say to that?

1224
00:52:31,287 --> 00:52:34,534
- Already speaking casually back then?
- He was speaking casually, and I was still...

1225
00:52:34,534 --> 00:52:36,588
[Caught the opportunity]
You had just met him though?

1226
00:52:36,588 --> 00:52:38,344
Hey, we saw each other
during the script reading too.

1227
00:52:38,344 --> 00:52:41,797
- That's right.
- We did the reading together and ate too.

1228
00:52:41,797 --> 00:52:45,800
You're really trying to ruin me more and more.

1229
00:52:45,800 --> 00:52:47,101
[Eun Tak makes the Grim Reaper sweat]
Oh, I thought...

1230
00:52:47,101 --> 00:52:51,014
you were talking about the
very first time you met him.

1231
00:52:51,014 --> 00:52:54,107
- So I had nothing to say.
- Why, why?

1232
00:52:54,107 --> 00:52:57,224
- What are you supposed to say to that?
- Someone like you who is good at empathizing?

1233
00:52:57,224 --> 00:53:00,613
- So I empathized and said, "Really?"
- Yeah, you probably said something like that.

1234
00:53:00,613 --> 00:53:04,106
I said, "Really?" and then he suddenly
looked straight at me at that "Really?"

1235
00:53:04,106 --> 00:53:06,892
[A wave of anxiety hits]
Go Eun, seriously! Dong Wook, it's true.

1236
00:53:06,892 --> 00:53:09,774
Then he said something you could never imagine.
Guess what?

1237
00:53:09,774 --> 00:53:13,220
He probably thought the word
"Really?" was unnecessary.

1238
00:53:13,220 --> 00:53:15,597
- You really know him well!
- Did I... maybe...

1239
00:53:15,597 --> 00:53:18,331
Did I say, "Of course it's real.
You think it's fake?"

1240
00:53:18,331 --> 00:53:21,537
Did I say, "Of course it's real.
You think it's fake?"

1241
00:53:21,537 --> 00:53:26,630
[He perfectly figured out
his past self from that day]

1242
00:53:26,630 --> 00:53:29,903
You know yourself really well.

1243
00:53:29,903 --> 00:53:31,863
- You were like...
- Ah, I'm really sorry.

1244
00:53:31,863 --> 00:53:34,517
- I'm sorry. Even now, I'd like to apologize.
- Well...

1245
00:53:34,517 --> 00:53:38,157
So, in his way of thinking,
"Really?" is just unnecessary...

1246
00:53:38,157 --> 00:53:40,390
Right, so when I said, "Really?"

1247
00:53:40,390 --> 00:53:42,358
He suddenly stopped what he was doing
and looked at me.

1248
00:53:42,358 --> 00:53:46,292
"Really?"
"Of course it's real. You think it's fake?"

1249
00:53:46,292 --> 00:53:47,941
- Do you think it'd be fake?
- Fake?

1250
00:53:47,941 --> 00:53:50,712
He said something...
and that's when I realized it.

1251
00:53:50,712 --> 00:53:53,194
But stop it. It's not that funny.

1252
00:53:54,305 --> 00:53:57,220
My stomach hurts...
because I'm laughing so hard.

1253
00:53:57,220 --> 00:53:58,476
This is so fun, though.

1254
00:53:58,476 --> 00:54:01,045
- Did you order soju?
- Yeah.

1255
00:54:01,045 --> 00:54:03,297
- This is dried pollack seaweed soup.
- Wow!

1256
00:54:03,297 --> 00:54:04,712
Have some seaweed soup first
to warm and soothe your stomach...

1257
00:54:04,712 --> 00:54:06,752
[Warm pollack seaweed soup to warm you up]
- Ah, first? - Wow, this alone looks delicious.

1258
00:54:06,752 --> 00:54:08,551
Hey, look at this!

1259
00:54:08,551 --> 00:54:11,686
- Is this mulhoe?
- Yeah, it's mulhoe.

1260
00:54:11,686 --> 00:54:15,189
[Fresh mulhoe with a size unlike any other]
- This is insane. - Wow, there's quite a lot.

1261
00:54:15,189 --> 00:54:16,991
- This comes out before the main raw fish.
- Wow!

1262
00:54:16,991 --> 00:54:18,644
Sea cucumber and sea squirt.

1263
00:54:18,644 --> 00:54:22,030
These are wild sea cucumber and sea squirt
caught in Tongyeong, and this is herring.

1264
00:54:22,030 --> 00:54:23,664
[Sea cucumber, sea squirt & herring]
Wow, thank you.

1265
00:54:23,664 --> 00:54:25,256
[The brows of truth]
I'll enjoy the food.

1266
00:54:25,256 --> 00:54:29,560
- I really, really love sea squirt.
- Oh, really?

1267
00:54:29,560 --> 00:54:31,272
[Go Eun's favorite:
fresh orange-colored sea squirt]

1268
00:54:31,272 --> 00:54:33,808
- Isn't this going to take like an hour or two?
- Yeah.

1269
00:54:33,808 --> 00:54:36,453
We make this sauce twice a year.

1270
00:54:36,453 --> 00:54:37,849
It goes well with raw fish.

1271
00:54:37,849 --> 00:54:41,544
- It's Gangwon-do Province's kkamakjang sauce.
- Oh, that's right.

1272
00:54:41,544 --> 00:54:42,954
[Looks delicious]
Wow...

1273
00:54:42,954 --> 00:54:45,314
- We would've really regretted not coming here.
- Wow...

1274
00:54:45,314 --> 00:54:46,511
Enjoy your meal.

1275
00:54:46,511 --> 00:54:48,021
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

1276
00:54:48,021 --> 00:54:52,029
[The first feast of the Goblin family,
filled with the scent of the sea]

1277
00:54:52,029 --> 00:54:54,898
Alright, everyone, cheers.

1278
00:54:54,898 --> 00:54:57,465
[Dong Wook and In Na toast with seaweed soup]
- Cheers. - You two should do it with alcohol.

1279
00:54:57,465 --> 00:54:58,870
Cheers.

1280
00:54:58,870 --> 00:55:01,584
We're really drinking during the day, huh?

1281
00:55:04,075 --> 00:55:05,502
Wow.

1282
00:55:05,502 --> 00:55:07,842
- Then I'll portion out the mulhoe.
- Oh, wow.

1283
00:55:07,842 --> 00:55:09,977
Is it sweet?

1284
00:55:09,977 --> 00:55:11,264
[So sweet]
Oh, wow.

1285
00:55:11,264 --> 00:55:14,415
Ten years ago, you said soju tasted so bitter.

1286
00:55:14,415 --> 00:55:15,550
- Go Eun did?
- No, I didn't.

1287
00:55:15,550 --> 00:55:16,744
- At the pojangmacha scene.
- Oh.

1288
00:55:16,744 --> 00:55:17,944
Oh.

1289
00:55:17,944 --> 00:55:20,734
Alright, cheers among adults.

1290
00:55:21,638 --> 00:55:22,782
Are you going to be okay...

1291
00:55:22,782 --> 00:55:25,763
[20-year-old Eun Tak, who became an adult
in the drama, having her first-ever soju]

1292
00:55:25,763 --> 00:55:27,990
It's romantic.

1293
00:55:27,990 --> 00:55:30,064
Ugh, it's bitter.

1294
00:55:30,064 --> 00:55:33,132
- Is soju normally like this?
- All alcohol is bitter at first.

1295
00:55:33,132 --> 00:55:35,473
When it starts tasting sweet,
that's when you really become an adult.

1296
00:55:35,473 --> 00:55:37,271
Then I'll have one more!

1297
00:55:37,271 --> 00:55:38,383
Fill it up!

1298
00:55:38,383 --> 00:55:42,695
[The first soju that only tasted bitter
somehow lingers sweetly today]

1299
00:55:42,695 --> 00:55:46,117
- Wow.
- Is it sweet?

1300
00:55:46,117 --> 00:55:48,101
Oh, wow.

1301
00:55:49,655 --> 00:55:51,472
Alright, let's dig in.

1302
00:55:51,472 --> 00:55:53,712
I'll enjoy the food.

1303
00:55:53,712 --> 00:55:55,656
[Go Eun starts with her favorite sea squirt]

1304
00:55:55,656 --> 00:55:59,327
[A refreshing ocean flavor hits instantly]

1305
00:55:59,327 --> 00:56:01,520
[Slurps up the kkamakjang sauce]

1306
00:56:02,930 --> 00:56:04,465
Wow!

1307
00:56:04,465 --> 00:56:06,849
- It's good, right?
- This sauce is so good.

1308
00:56:06,849 --> 00:56:08,870
[Curious]

1309
00:56:08,870 --> 00:56:10,096
What did she say this was again?

1310
00:56:10,096 --> 00:56:11,837
Herring.

1311
00:56:11,837 --> 00:56:14,814
It's really good
when you eat this with the sauce.

1312
00:56:16,714 --> 00:56:19,287
Wow, the sauce is really good.

1313
00:56:21,085 --> 00:56:22,330
- The sauce is really good.
- Yeah.

1314
00:56:22,330 --> 00:56:24,162
[More and more impressed]

1315
00:56:24,162 --> 00:56:26,497
She said earlier that
she makes it twice a year.

1316
00:56:26,497 --> 00:56:27,840
[With the raw fish, and with the sauce]
I mean, that sauce...

1317
00:56:27,840 --> 00:56:28,862
Okay, okay.

1318
00:56:28,862 --> 00:56:31,448
[Hurry, hurry!]
Okay, wait a second.

1319
00:56:31,448 --> 00:56:34,532
- Wait, wait a second.
- Hurry, hurry!

1320
00:56:34,532 --> 00:56:37,738
- Eat it, eat it quickly.
- Hurry.

1321
00:56:37,738 --> 00:56:39,975
[After downing a shot of soju first]

1322
00:56:41,058 --> 00:56:42,204
[It's the perfect sweet and refreshing taste]

1323
00:56:42,204 --> 00:56:43,671
- I'm going.
- Mulhoe is good, right?

1324
00:56:43,671 --> 00:56:46,326
I'll be back, I'll be back!

1325
00:56:47,557 --> 00:56:49,477
[A taste journey to a delicious world]

1326
00:56:49,477 --> 00:56:50,732
Yum!

1327
00:56:50,732 --> 00:56:51,851
[It's so good, right?]
It's good.

1328
00:56:51,851 --> 00:56:54,949
So good. It goes so well with the sauce.

1329
00:56:54,949 --> 00:56:56,331
[The perfect pair: herring raw fish and sauce]
This and this.

1330
00:56:56,331 --> 00:56:57,355
- Oh, yeah?
- Yeah.

1331
00:56:57,355 --> 00:57:00,303
[Serious]
- Could you mix it a little more? - Like this?

1332
00:57:00,303 --> 00:57:02,123
[Cute]
- Like this? - Yeah.

1333
00:57:02,123 --> 00:57:04,911
With the herring like this, just a little bit.

1334
00:57:04,911 --> 00:57:06,964
Now, try eating it like that.

1335
00:57:08,362 --> 00:57:10,734
It's insanely good, right?

1336
00:57:10,734 --> 00:57:12,901
The herring is good.

1337
00:57:13,705 --> 00:57:17,200
[Next, trying the mulhoe]

1338
00:57:17,200 --> 00:57:19,769
The mulhoe sauce is good too.

1339
00:57:19,769 --> 00:57:22,074
- What if we hadn't come here?
- Right.

1340
00:57:22,074 --> 00:57:24,090
[Spicy ocean flavor fills your mouth]
- Ah, the mulhoe is good. - Yeah.

1341
00:57:24,090 --> 00:57:26,640
Eun Tak, try some sea squirt.

1342
00:57:27,515 --> 00:57:30,688
[Still delicious even after eating it again]
- She's eating it. She already ate some. - Yum!

1343
00:57:30,688 --> 00:57:32,332
You should really try the sea squirt.

1344
00:57:32,332 --> 00:57:35,061
- I really...
- Can't you eat it?

1345
00:57:35,061 --> 00:57:38,341
I thought I wouldn't be able to eat
sea squirt, so I never tried it.

1346
00:57:38,341 --> 00:57:39,493
- Should I try?
- Oh, really?

1347
00:57:39,493 --> 00:57:40,518
Yeah.

1348
00:57:40,518 --> 00:57:44,015
- I thought it might be kind of soft and mushy.
- So you don't like this kind of texture.

1349
00:57:44,015 --> 00:57:48,321
Then dip this generously
in red chili sauce and try it.

1350
00:57:49,099 --> 00:57:50,371
Wasn't false sea squirt better?

1351
00:57:50,371 --> 00:57:52,840
- False sea squirt is better.
- Right, false sea squirt is better.

1352
00:57:52,840 --> 00:57:55,332
- False sea squirt has less of a bitter taste.
- Right.

1353
00:57:55,332 --> 00:57:59,016
[How is it? It's good, right?]

1354
00:57:59,016 --> 00:58:01,092
Why do people like this?

1355
00:58:02,732 --> 00:58:04,964
- I don't really taste a specific flavor.
- Just the taste of the ocean?

1356
00:58:04,964 --> 00:58:06,853
The taste of the ocean,
a slightly bitter taste.

1357
00:58:06,853 --> 00:58:09,932
[A strong taste of the raw ocean]

1358
00:58:09,932 --> 00:58:11,305
[The main assorted raw fish finally arrives]
Let's add sesame oil.

1359
00:58:11,305 --> 00:58:13,761
- Wow, that's a lot...
- The main dish is here.

1360
00:58:13,761 --> 00:58:15,231
- This is black porgy.
- Okay.

1361
00:58:15,231 --> 00:58:18,886
This is wild flounder, and this is maraemi.

1362
00:58:18,886 --> 00:58:20,538
[Flounder, Maraemi, Black porgy]

1363
00:58:20,538 --> 00:58:22,203
[An entirely different level of brilliance,
a platter of assorted raw fish]

1364
00:58:22,203 --> 00:58:25,373
- These three fins are the most delicious parts.
- The fin part separately?

1365
00:58:25,373 --> 00:58:26,753
- So you set them aside separately.
- Really?

1366
00:58:26,753 --> 00:58:27,884
A premium cut...

1367
00:58:27,884 --> 00:58:30,946
- Can I try it?
- Sure, go for it.

1368
00:58:32,675 --> 00:58:35,680
[A chewy piece of black porgy]

1369
00:58:35,680 --> 00:58:39,183
Try dipping the black porgy
straight in wasabi soy sauce.

1370
00:58:39,183 --> 00:58:41,295
Eat it that way.

1371
00:58:44,962 --> 00:58:46,692
[Dipping it deeply into soy sauce]
So, if I put in a lot of wasabi...

1372
00:58:46,692 --> 00:58:49,005
- No, no, not that much.
- It's salty.

1373
00:58:49,005 --> 00:58:50,852
[In a grown-up tone]
It's salty!

1374
00:58:50,852 --> 00:58:52,042
[Bursts out laughing]

1375
00:58:52,042 --> 00:58:54,936
- Why? Did I sound too much like a dad?
- Yeah.

1376
00:58:54,936 --> 00:58:57,836
You sounded like you were talking to a cat.

1377
00:59:00,618 --> 00:59:05,079
[Chewy raw fish that goes down smoothly]

1378
00:59:05,079 --> 00:59:07,371
[It's so delicious! Yum, yum]

1379
00:59:07,371 --> 00:59:10,641
- The sauce is amazing!
- Yeah.

1380
00:59:10,641 --> 00:59:12,590
[A sip of mulhoe broth]

1381
00:59:13,710 --> 00:59:15,957
[A bite of abalone porridge]

1382
00:59:15,957 --> 00:59:21,199
[Diving into the fresh taste of the sea]

1383
00:59:21,199 --> 00:59:23,700
[She's eating well]

1384
00:59:23,700 --> 00:59:25,478
- What did she say this was?
- Black porgy.

1385
00:59:25,478 --> 00:59:26,482
- Oh, black porgy.
- It's kind of like this.

1386
00:59:26,482 --> 00:59:28,552
It's one of the four top breams.

1387
00:59:28,552 --> 00:59:30,085
- Black porgy.
- Eat up a lot.

1388
00:59:30,085 --> 00:59:32,710
Why is it called black porgy?

1389
00:59:32,710 --> 00:59:34,584
Because it's F.

1390
00:59:37,147 --> 00:59:40,752
[An emotional black F-porgy]

1391
00:59:40,752 --> 00:59:44,188
Why is it called black porgy?
Fishing expert, tell us quickly.

1392
00:59:44,188 --> 00:59:46,152
[Even the fishing expert is flustered]
Fishing expert Dr. Gong, tell us quickly.

1393
00:59:46,152 --> 00:59:47,777
Why is it called black porgy?

1394
00:59:47,777 --> 00:59:49,798
Look it up on social media,
it has a really "vibe-y" feel.

1395
00:59:49,798 --> 00:59:50,863
[Glares]
Really?

1396
00:59:50,863 --> 00:59:53,359
Ah, too late, too late.

1397
00:59:53,359 --> 00:59:54,424
I already did that once.

1398
00:59:54,424 --> 00:59:57,064
I thought to myself,
"I shouldn't have said that."

1399
00:59:57,064 --> 00:59:59,467
- Then...
- Yeah.

1400
00:59:59,467 --> 01:00:02,115
- Another option comes up?
- No, I'll guess your MBTI.

1401
01:00:02,115 --> 01:00:04,424
Because we didn't know
each other's MBTI back then.

1402
01:00:04,424 --> 01:00:07,285
Yeah. You think I've ever taken an MBTI test?

1403
01:00:07,285 --> 01:00:09,947
[Dong Wook: ISTP, versatile troubleshooter]
ISTP.

1404
01:00:09,947 --> 01:00:12,767
I just say I'm ABCD, that's all.

1405
01:00:13,576 --> 01:00:16,872
He's not E? He's I?

1406
01:00:16,872 --> 01:00:18,193
E?

1407
01:00:18,193 --> 01:00:20,194
Maybe I'm right on the border?
Between E and I...

1408
01:00:20,194 --> 01:00:23,099
- Like 49 to 51.
- That could be.

1409
01:00:23,099 --> 01:00:26,016
[Dong Wook is definitely a T]
Yeah, that sounds right.

1410
01:00:26,016 --> 01:00:28,803
Then I'll guess your blood type, at your level.

1411
01:00:28,803 --> 01:00:30,149
Okay.

1412
01:00:30,149 --> 01:00:32,752
- "At your level."
- You're totally just playing along with him.

1413
01:00:32,752 --> 01:00:34,951
- Type B.
- Yeah.

1414
01:00:34,951 --> 01:00:37,440
- He's Type B. Isn't he obviously Type B?
- Oh, Type B.

1415
01:00:37,440 --> 01:00:38,749
It's written all over his face
that he's Type B.

1416
01:00:38,749 --> 01:00:40,687
Type B people are the most charming.

1417
01:00:40,687 --> 01:00:43,501
- Yeah, that's right.
- Are you messing with him?

1418
01:00:43,501 --> 01:00:45,339
[I'm a Type B woman too, hehe]
I'm Type B too.

1419
01:00:45,339 --> 01:00:47,020
- Type B people are the most charming.
- He's Type B.

1420
01:00:47,020 --> 01:00:49,880
- Female Type B and male Type B are different.
- Really?

1421
01:00:49,880 --> 01:00:52,575
- Oh, forget it.
- What does blood have to do with this?

1422
01:00:52,575 --> 01:00:54,271
Female Type B is charming.

1423
01:00:54,271 --> 01:00:57,230
[The charming B-est couple]
Oh, that's right. Type B people are charming.

1424
01:00:57,230 --> 01:01:02,449
Women like Type B men when they're young.

1425
01:01:02,449 --> 01:01:04,679
- Why?
- Bad boys!

1426
01:01:04,679 --> 01:01:08,363
After liking bad boys and growing older,

1427
01:01:08,363 --> 01:01:10,365
you realize Type A men are actually good.

1428
01:01:10,365 --> 01:01:12,498
- Type A?
- Yeah.

1429
01:01:14,924 --> 01:01:17,995
Alright, enough. Let's eat.

1430
01:01:17,995 --> 01:01:20,797
[According to himself, a charming Type A man]

1431
01:01:20,797 --> 01:01:23,451
Ah, the timing was really funny.

1432
01:01:23,451 --> 01:01:27,284
But I've always felt this...

1433
01:01:27,284 --> 01:01:29,657
- All four of us are so nice!
- Yeah.

1434
01:01:29,657 --> 01:01:30,878
[The youngest one's cute compliment]

1435
01:01:30,878 --> 01:01:33,527
- I mean, personality-wise...
- This is really cute right now.

1436
01:01:33,527 --> 01:01:35,318
- Really? All four of us are really nice?
- Yeah.

1437
01:01:35,318 --> 01:01:38,265
Our personalities are all different,
but we're kind-hearted.

1438
01:01:38,265 --> 01:01:39,285
- That's right.
- That's right.

1439
01:01:39,285 --> 01:01:40,486
- That's true.
- We're all a little soft-hearted.

1440
01:01:40,486 --> 01:01:43,003
And we all care for others in our own ways.

1441
01:01:43,003 --> 01:01:45,118
[The Goblin family taking care of each other]
- That's right. - Yeah, that's right.

1442
01:01:45,118 --> 01:01:47,658
But something I really feel sometimes is...

1443
01:01:47,658 --> 01:01:51,319
One day, Eun Tak suddenly
calls me out of nowhere.

1444
01:01:51,319 --> 01:01:54,308
And she goes, "Are you doing okay these days?"

1445
01:01:54,308 --> 01:01:55,872
"Yeah, why?"

1446
01:01:55,872 --> 01:01:58,347
"I was just wondering
if you're feeling at ease."

1447
01:01:58,347 --> 01:02:00,856
- Really?
- Yeah, she checks on me like that sometimes.

1448
01:02:00,856 --> 01:02:02,021
Why do you do that?

1449
01:02:02,021 --> 01:02:04,308
- Because he works so much.
- Right.

1450
01:02:04,308 --> 01:02:08,754
I live without really noticing it,
even when I'm busy.

1451
01:02:08,754 --> 01:02:11,371
But when Eun Tak asks me that sometimes,

1452
01:02:11,371 --> 01:02:14,268
I think, "Am I really okay right now?"
I end up asking myself that.

1453
01:02:14,268 --> 01:02:16,215
To check on himself once in a while.

1454
01:02:16,215 --> 01:02:17,737
So I say, "Yeah, I'm okay."

1455
01:02:17,737 --> 01:02:19,816
- "I can handle it."
- If you're too busy and only work,

1456
01:02:19,816 --> 01:02:21,693
you might not even notice yourself.

1457
01:02:21,693 --> 01:02:26,630
- You might not realize it and then suddenly...
- If burnout suddenly hits you...

1458
01:02:26,630 --> 01:02:30,179
you might get caught off guard
without being prepared.

1459
01:02:30,179 --> 01:02:33,063
She always says things like that to me.

1460
01:02:33,063 --> 01:02:37,285
Right, who works as hard as you do, Dong Wook?

1461
01:02:37,285 --> 01:02:38,488
- There are many.
- Without taking breaks.

1462
01:02:38,488 --> 01:02:41,213
With hardly any time to rest in between...

1463
01:02:41,213 --> 01:02:43,496
Goblin is actually the one who works the least.

1464
01:02:43,496 --> 01:02:46,515
Why? He worked really hard this past year.

1465
01:02:46,515 --> 01:02:48,207
Of course, I worked hard for a year.

1466
01:02:48,207 --> 01:02:49,728
That's right, you did well.

1467
01:02:49,728 --> 01:02:52,549
[Well done, Goblin! You're the best!]
You're the best!

1468
01:02:52,549 --> 01:02:54,767
[Out of emotion]
Let's go now.

1469
01:02:56,832 --> 01:02:58,564
Home? Or back to the accommodation?

1470
01:02:58,564 --> 01:03:00,052
- Home.
- Oh, Seoul?

1471
01:03:00,052 --> 01:03:02,316
- I think we've done everything we can.
- He's already tired.

1472
01:03:02,316 --> 01:03:04,911
Let's drink more quickly,
he's saying he's going home.

1473
01:03:04,911 --> 01:03:07,951
[We should drink more quickly!]

1474
01:03:09,899 --> 01:03:11,962
No wonder you were drinking so much earlier.

1475
01:03:11,962 --> 01:03:13,163
[In Na fills her own glass]

1476
01:03:13,163 --> 01:03:16,159
- What are you doing?
- I'm curious what it tastes like.

1477
01:03:16,159 --> 01:03:17,398
Cheers first, then drink.

1478
01:03:17,398 --> 01:03:19,719
- Yeah, if we're going to drink anyway...
- Cheers.

1479
01:03:19,719 --> 01:03:22,044
[If we're drinking, let's all cheer]
Look at him taking care of her again.

1480
01:03:25,960 --> 01:03:28,140
I can't drive.

1481
01:03:28,737 --> 01:03:30,177
I can't drive.

1482
01:03:30,177 --> 01:03:31,472
[Snorts]

1483
01:03:31,472 --> 01:03:34,242
Dong Wook, I'm sorry.

1484
01:03:35,390 --> 01:03:37,178
I can't drive,
I think you have to do it, Dong Wook.

1485
01:03:37,178 --> 01:03:40,263
- This is so funny.
- This is annoying.

1486
01:03:40,263 --> 01:03:44,265
I wasn't even planning to make you drive,
but saying it like that annoys me.

1487
01:03:44,265 --> 01:03:46,483
[Sorry]

1488
01:03:46,483 --> 01:03:48,976
I'm really happy.

1489
01:03:48,976 --> 01:03:51,832
- Are you really happy?
- Yeah.

1490
01:03:51,832 --> 01:03:53,805
["I'm happy right now in this moment"]
This place is happiness for me.

1491
01:03:53,805 --> 01:03:55,999
Yeah, what could be happier than this?

1492
01:03:55,999 --> 01:03:58,806
- Nothing, nothing.
- Right.

1493
01:03:58,806 --> 01:04:02,464
Finally, we're going to see our accommodation.

1494
01:04:02,464 --> 01:04:05,798
[Heading to the accommodation]
The place we'll stay for a day.

1495
01:04:05,798 --> 01:04:09,685
[Visual inspection]

1496
01:04:09,685 --> 01:04:14,804
- Wow, my face got tanned already.
- Really? Then we all got tanned.

1497
01:04:14,804 --> 01:04:17,277
[Did everyone's face get tanned?]

1498
01:04:17,277 --> 01:04:19,786
[Rummaging]

1499
01:04:19,786 --> 01:04:22,755
- It did. It really did.
- Put on some sunscreen.

1500
01:04:22,755 --> 01:04:23,975
- Oh, you startled me.
- Wow.

1501
01:04:23,975 --> 01:04:26,551
- It looks so fascinating.
- What is that? Is it sunscreen?

1502
01:04:26,551 --> 01:04:31,417
This sunscreen is also good
for your skin. So just...

1503
01:04:31,417 --> 01:04:33,559
So... how do I put it?

1504
01:04:33,559 --> 01:04:35,137
[Pat pat]
- Don't rub it in... - Yeah.

1505
01:04:35,137 --> 01:04:36,917
[A face smaller than a hand]
- Pat it in? - Like this?

1506
01:04:36,917 --> 01:04:40,437
[Pat pat]
It's just... the sun is too strong.

1507
01:04:40,437 --> 01:04:43,211
[Everyone doing careful skincare together]
This way, your makeup won't come off.

1508
01:04:43,211 --> 01:04:46,228
[Focused]

1509
01:04:46,228 --> 01:04:47,998
- Are you okay?
- What?

1510
01:04:47,998 --> 01:04:50,724
- I mean, your cheek.
- Oh, you're patting your face way too hard.

1511
01:04:50,724 --> 01:04:53,357
Your cheek must hurt.

1512
01:04:53,357 --> 01:04:56,639
[The goblin's immortal skincare routine]

1513
01:04:58,105 --> 01:05:00,013
[Stare]

1514
01:05:00,013 --> 01:05:03,419
Wow, that bakery looks like it has great bread.

1515
01:05:03,419 --> 01:05:05,920
Should we buy some?

1516
01:05:05,920 --> 01:05:09,972
- They say... they bake happiness.
- That's sweet.

1517
01:05:09,972 --> 01:05:12,672
If you want bread, just buy some.

1518
01:05:12,672 --> 01:05:17,266
My sister's husband was driving,
and my sister was sitting next to him.

1519
01:05:17,266 --> 01:05:18,526
There was a bakery over there,

1520
01:05:18,526 --> 01:05:21,708
and she said, "Oh, I want some bread.
Let's buy some bread to take home,"

1521
01:05:21,708 --> 01:05:25,067
but he said, "No, I don't want bread,"
and just kept driving straight.

1522
01:05:25,067 --> 01:05:26,645
So your sister was really upset?

1523
01:05:26,645 --> 01:05:30,663
But just now when I said,
"That bread looks good,"

1524
01:05:30,663 --> 01:05:32,915
he immediately said, "Should we buy some?"
That's the right answer.

1525
01:05:32,915 --> 01:05:34,863
- Exactly. At least say it like that.
- That's how you should say it.

1526
01:05:34,863 --> 01:05:37,124
- Yeah.
- I said it because there's a camera.

1527
01:05:37,124 --> 01:05:39,340
- Don't lie.
- No, that just...

1528
01:05:39,340 --> 01:05:42,251
[Rejecting compliments]
- came out naturally. - Instant reaction.

1529
01:05:42,929 --> 01:05:47,058
He always does that
when he gets praised for something he did.

1530
01:05:47,058 --> 01:05:50,199
[Someone who gets awkward with compliments]
- Ah, I hate this. - He's always like that.

1531
01:05:50,199 --> 01:05:54,311
- Stop complimenting me. It's so uncomfortable.
- I should really praise him a lot.

1532
01:05:54,311 --> 01:05:55,869
We like doing things people don't like.

1533
01:05:55,869 --> 01:05:59,656
[Planning to trap him in compliment jail]
We need to get him used to it.

1534
01:05:59,656 --> 01:06:01,166
I think we're here now?

1535
01:06:01,166 --> 01:06:04,632
[They arrived before they knew it]

1536
01:06:04,632 --> 01:06:05,903
Oh, I think this is the house?

1537
01:06:05,903 --> 01:06:08,110
- Oh, this is the place.
- Oh, this is the house?

1538
01:06:08,110 --> 01:06:11,517
[The Goblin House
located in front of a quiet sea]

1539
01:06:12,816 --> 01:06:16,756
Oh! Isn't that the door that leads to Canada?

1540
01:06:16,756 --> 01:06:19,862
- Isn't that the door that leads to Canada?
- Oh!

1541
01:06:19,862 --> 01:06:21,583
[The red door summoned to the East Sea]

1542
01:06:25,542 --> 01:06:26,649
Oh, here it is.

1543
01:06:26,649 --> 01:06:28,262
[Heading to today's accommodation
with excited steps]

1544
01:06:28,262 --> 01:06:31,129
- This way...
- Ah, it's so cute.

1545
01:06:31,129 --> 01:06:34,790
- We go in here, right?
- Oh, here it is.

1546
01:06:34,790 --> 01:06:37,295
"Fairy appearance area." Right?

1547
01:06:37,295 --> 01:06:40,433
[Fairy appearance area]

1548
01:06:40,433 --> 01:06:43,980
[Eun Tak came to Quebec, Canada
through the red door following the Goblin]

1549
01:06:43,980 --> 01:06:47,175
By the way, what is that sign?

1550
01:06:47,175 --> 01:06:48,773
"Fairy appearance area."

1551
01:06:48,773 --> 01:06:52,217
Here? Wow, do fairies appear here?

1552
01:06:52,217 --> 01:06:54,480
You must like that.

1553
01:06:54,480 --> 01:06:58,633
- Why would I like that?
- Fairy appearance. You met a fairy!

1554
01:06:58,633 --> 01:07:00,543
Tinker Bell.

1555
01:07:00,543 --> 01:07:02,401
Right, it says fairy appearance.

1556
01:07:02,401 --> 01:07:05,107
- Hey, this one pulls... you pull this...
- I'll pull it for you, Dong Wook.

1557
01:07:05,107 --> 01:07:08,324
- Pull the door.
- Go through that gap.

1558
01:07:08,324 --> 01:07:10,857
[Leaving the red door for the fairy door]
- Go ahead inside. - Go in first.

1559
01:07:10,857 --> 01:07:12,450
Go ahead.

1560
01:07:12,450 --> 01:07:15,336
- The luggage carriers go in first.
- Where is it?

1561
01:07:15,336 --> 01:07:16,729
- I think we just go forward.
- In Na, you go in.

1562
01:07:16,729 --> 01:07:19,436
- Is this the house?
- Right here, this is the house.

1563
01:07:19,436 --> 01:07:21,734
It's pretty!

1564
01:07:22,678 --> 01:07:27,785
[Introducing today's accommodation]

1565
01:07:27,785 --> 01:07:33,435
[with the blue sea spread out before them]

1566
01:07:39,019 --> 01:07:41,250
[The Goblin House where 2 days and 1 night
of memories will be made]

1567
01:07:41,250 --> 01:07:44,270
- Nice.
- Wow, it's really nice.

1568
01:07:44,270 --> 01:07:47,863
We can have a party here later.

1569
01:07:48,870 --> 01:07:51,820
[When night falls on the Goblin House...]

1570
01:07:51,820 --> 01:07:53,965
[Whoosh]

1571
01:07:53,965 --> 01:07:57,265
[A colorful chat session is about to ignite]

1572
01:07:57,265 --> 01:07:59,538
This is so funny.

1573
01:08:00,490 --> 01:08:02,965
[We're really going to have fun, Goblin-style]

1574
01:08:04,336 --> 01:08:06,510
It's pretty!

1575
01:08:08,324 --> 01:08:09,551
Huh?

1576
01:08:10,959 --> 01:08:12,717
What is this?

1577
01:08:12,717 --> 01:08:14,911
- Goblin.
- Yeah?

1578
01:08:14,911 --> 01:08:16,547
What was this again?

1579
01:08:16,547 --> 01:08:17,937
Let me see. I'll check... what is it?

1580
01:08:17,937 --> 01:08:19,124
- Look, this was...
- It's the same as

1581
01:08:19,124 --> 01:08:22,363
Goblin Kim Shin's house password?

1582
01:08:23,456 --> 01:08:29,741
[A note attached in front of the door]

1583
01:08:29,741 --> 01:08:31,117
Let me see. I'll check... what is it?

1584
01:08:31,117 --> 01:08:32,194
- Look, this was...
- It's the same as

1585
01:08:32,194 --> 01:08:34,207
Goblin Kim Shin's house password?

1586
01:08:34,207 --> 01:08:36,452
- 1004!
- Oh, right.

1587
01:08:36,452 --> 01:08:38,717
- Really?
- Yeah, that's right. 1004.

1588
01:08:38,717 --> 01:08:40,768
Because we always passed through
without entering it.

1589
01:08:40,768 --> 01:08:42,830
Hey, Eun Tak! Wow...

1590
01:08:42,830 --> 01:08:43,943
[So impressive]
Right, we went through it,

1591
01:08:43,943 --> 01:08:45,353
- so we never remembered it.
- Right, back then...

1592
01:08:45,353 --> 01:08:48,157
- Oh, that's right.
- Yeah.

1593
01:08:48,157 --> 01:08:49,988
It should be four digits, right?

1594
01:08:49,988 --> 01:08:53,983
[Even back then, they didn't know the password]
You probably pressed the star at the end.

1595
01:08:53,983 --> 01:08:58,287
You two don't know the password?

1596
01:08:58,287 --> 01:09:01,053
Because we've never entered
by pressing the numbers.

1597
01:09:03,737 --> 01:09:08,804
[Instead of a password, teleportation]

1598
01:09:08,804 --> 01:09:12,659
[Only Deok Hwa knew the password]
- Tell me the front door password. - 1004!

1599
01:09:13,926 --> 01:09:15,320
[Passed with the help of
former resident Go Eun]

1600
01:09:15,320 --> 01:09:19,781
What is this? It looks so interesting.

1601
01:09:20,954 --> 01:09:24,191
[Introducing today's Goblin House]

1602
01:09:24,191 --> 01:09:28,764
[A cozy living room]

1603
01:09:31,223 --> 01:09:35,945
[With the blue sea captured inside]

1604
01:09:35,945 --> 01:09:37,691
Let's see.

1605
01:09:37,691 --> 01:09:41,164
- Oh!
- Whoa!

1606
01:09:44,124 --> 01:09:46,880
- Oh my! What is this?
- What is this?

1607
01:09:46,880 --> 01:09:50,707
- Hey, everyone, come here!
- This is hilarious.

1608
01:09:50,707 --> 01:09:51,808
What is it?

1609
01:09:51,808 --> 01:09:54,055
- Yeah, look at this.
- What?

1610
01:09:56,758 --> 01:10:00,404
Whoa... there's Eun Tak's exam ID card.

1611
01:10:15,844 --> 01:10:17,545
Alright, congratulations
on the 10th anniversary!

1612
01:10:17,545 --> 01:10:20,071
- Alright, let's have a great time today.
- Congratulations!

1613
01:10:20,071 --> 01:10:22,505
- Let's go!
- Have fun, and don't fight.

1614
01:10:22,505 --> 01:10:23,659
[A party of ours filled with
laughter and excitement]

1615
01:10:23,659 --> 01:10:25,292
I'm suddenly getting really excited.

1616
01:10:25,292 --> 01:10:27,216
Oh, boy.

1617
01:10:27,216 --> 01:10:28,680
[Taking things out]

1618
01:10:28,680 --> 01:10:29,913
[And taking out more]

1619
01:10:29,913 --> 01:10:31,680
Wow! There's so much food.

1620
01:10:31,680 --> 01:10:35,124
- Did you bring this seaweed?
- Yeah, because that seaweed was really good.

1621
01:10:35,124 --> 01:10:36,598
[The ultimate J-goblin's flawless
ingredient preparation]

1622
01:10:36,598 --> 01:10:39,711
The pork shoulder will be quick,
but we're going to grill the pork belly whole.

1623
01:10:39,711 --> 01:10:41,369
Wow! Awesome!

1624
01:10:41,369 --> 01:10:43,383
[Chef Gong in charge of the main dish]
Wow, that looks good.

1625
01:10:43,383 --> 01:10:45,563
[And lighting the fire]

1626
01:10:45,563 --> 01:10:48,183
She said she's going to make
cucumber salad too.

1627
01:10:48,183 --> 01:10:49,919
[Keeping the fire going, making side dishes,
and cheering everyone on]

1628
01:10:49,919 --> 01:10:50,816
So cute.

1629
01:10:50,816 --> 01:10:53,874
- Everyone's pitching in.
- We just need to be good assistants.

1630
01:10:53,874 --> 01:10:55,832
Hurry, hurry!

1631
01:10:55,832 --> 01:10:57,364
- We're really short on time.
- Hurry...

1632
01:10:57,364 --> 01:10:59,040
We're out of time.

1633
01:10:59,040 --> 01:11:01,836
[Not much time left before the guests arrive]

1634
01:11:01,836 --> 01:11:03,996
What is this supposed to taste like?

1635
01:11:03,996 --> 01:11:06,356
Stop trying to force it. Just stay still.

1636
01:11:06,356 --> 01:11:10,829
- Ugh, what's wrong with you?
- Come on... just move over there.

1637
01:11:10,829 --> 01:11:13,369
[The Peach Couple ends up bickering again]
You two, don't fight.

1638
01:11:13,369 --> 01:11:15,927
Come on, heat up... The temperature
won't go up. This is bad.

1639
01:11:15,927 --> 01:11:19,116
[Even Goblin is in trouble?]
What exactly is he trying to do?

1640
01:11:19,116 --> 01:11:20,764
Why isn't the temperature going up?

1641
01:11:20,764 --> 01:11:22,538
Hey, mister! You have to close that
for the temperature to rise.

1642
01:11:22,538 --> 01:11:25,068
- Right, stop opening it.
- Will it heat up if you keep opening it?

1643
01:11:25,068 --> 01:11:26,439
Ugh, we'll never get to eat.

1644
01:11:26,439 --> 01:11:28,433
[While the Goblin Family
scrambles to get the party ready...]

1645
01:11:28,433 --> 01:11:30,020
Wow, it's the ocean!

1646
01:11:30,020 --> 01:11:31,643
Isn't this house gorgeous?

1647
01:11:31,643 --> 01:11:33,449
Ah, there it is.

1648
01:11:33,449 --> 01:11:36,860
[Three people approaching the Goblin house]
- Huh? - Hello.

1649
01:11:36,860 --> 01:11:38,201
[Familiar faces that instantly bring smiles]
- That's right. - That's right.

1650
01:11:38,201 --> 01:11:39,402
Hello.

1651
01:11:39,402 --> 01:11:41,070
- Hello.
- Like that!

1652
01:11:41,070 --> 01:11:42,296
Unbelievable!

1653
01:11:42,296 --> 01:11:43,890
[Park Kyung Hye as the Ghost Bride,
Lee El as Samshin]

1654
01:11:43,890 --> 01:11:45,022
[Kim Byung Chul as Park Joong Heon]

1655
01:11:45,022 --> 01:11:46,750
It's so good to see you!

1656
01:11:46,750 --> 01:11:48,883
[From four to seven,
the fun just got even bigger]

1657
01:11:48,883 --> 01:11:51,563
[Main event of the 10th anniversary party]
How about I give you all a quiz?

